Commentary: Ngidi starts off with a back of a length ball into the left-hander, Dimuth looks to tuck this one away but gets hit high on the thigh pad and the ball rolls to the off side.
Down the leg side, DM misses his tuck away.
Inward movement noticed! Another back of a length ball on middle and leg, Karunaratne looks to push this to the leg side but the ball nips into Dimuth and hits him on the thigh pad.
On off, pushed to the leg side.

FOUR! Sri Lanka and Karunaratne are underway and they do it with some style! Some width offered as this was outside off, the skipper camps back and punches this one through the cover region for a boundary. A good start for Lankans.
Dot to end! On off, pushed to the leg side. 4 from the first over.

3 LEG BYES! On the pads, Kusal looks to tuck this away but it comes off the thigh pad and goes past de Kock towards the fine leg region. The fielder gives it a chase and stops it before the ropes. Three leg byes collected.
Slightly straight and on the pads, flicked away to the right of fine leg for a couple.
FOUR! The skipper is off to a good start! Straight and on middle again, clipped to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Full ball and on off, DM works it through square leg and the call is for two. They collect two comfortably.
Back of a length on middle, blocked out.
BEATEN! A beauty to end the over! On a length on off, Karunaratne looks for the defensive stroke but misses it altogether.
A full delivery on off, Kusal pushes it back to the bowler.
On middle, pushed to the square leg region.
Good length on off, Perara pushes it towards mid on and the batters take off for a single. There is a throw at the striker's end but it is missed and the batters collect one more. Good running.
Slightly straight again, KP looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Back of a length ball on off, Kusal looks to work this one away but misses again to get hit on the pads.
Full ball on off, Perera looks to push this away but it takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads.
On a length on middle, Dimuth clips this through square leg and collects two runs as Ngidi runs across in the deep and stops this from crossing the ropes.
BEATEN! Ohhh...great bowling by Sipamla! Lands it on a length and around off, Karunaratne looks for the defensive stroke but the ball whizzes past his outside edge and into the keeper's mitts.
On off, pushed to the leg side.

EDGY FOUR! Not what the skipper was looking to do but he will be happy with the result! On a length on off, Dimuth looks to block this one out but it takes the outside edge and goes in between slips and gully into the third man boundary.
Bouncer on middle, Dimuth sits under this one.
FOUR! Boundary to end the over! An overpitched delivery and on off, Karunaratne clips this one through mid-wicket and it runs away to the ropes. A good over for the visitors. 10 runs off this.
Short of a length and on off, KP looks to defend but it takes the edge and goes to the point region.
Outside off, punched to covers for a single.
On off, played to the leg side.
On middle and leg, slightly behind the good length, the captain looks for the flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.

OUT! TIMBER! DRAGGED ON! The first wicket falls for the visitors and the captain, who had a good start has to walk back now! Karunaratne had a good start but unfortunately for the Lankans, he cannot continue on. Slightly shortish and outside off, Dimuth looks to push this one away but does not move his feet. The ball takes the inside edge and goes onto rattle the stumps behind him.
Outside off, Mendis looks to play at that but decides not to, right at the end. A good over for the Proteas comes to an end.
Overpitched around the off pole, Kusal pushes this to the mid off region.
On middle, worked to mid-wicket for a quick run.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! A freebie to Mendis and he opens his account in this game! A slow short ball outside off, Mendis slashes this one over the cover region to find the ropes.
Short ball around off, Mendis thinks of playing the pull but then decides against it. No Ball given.
FOUR! Beautifully played by Mendis! Slightly overpitched around the off pole, Mendis plays it with a straight bat and through mid off and the ball runs away to the ropes. Confident start by Kusal.
Length ball on off, pushed to the off side.
FOUR! Short ball outside off, Perera lofts this one over the cover region for a boundary. Kusal is not going to miss out on these.
On middle, nudged to square leg.
On middle, worked to square leg again.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Perera looks to cut but it takes the inside half of the bat and it goes past the leg stump. A couple taken as the ball rolls to fine leg.
One to end! On middle, worked through square leg.
On off, pushed to the off side.
An appeal for LBW but turned down! A back of a length ball on middle and leg, KP looks to tuck this away but misses to get hit on the pads. A loud appeal follows but no says the umpire.
FOUR! Perera has started off strongly! On a length on middle, Perera clips this one through the short fine leg region into the ropes.
Outside off, Kusal pushes this to point.

Well stopped by Anrich! On a length on off, Perera punches this one down the ground but Nortje hangs his foot out and blocks it out. Would have stung but nothing that someone like Nortje can't shake off.
What was that? The ball just zipped after pitching! On a length outside off, it takes off after pitching. De Kock does well to jump and get a hand to this one. Took everyone by surprise there.
Outside off, left alone.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a length on off, nips away slightly, Mendis looks to block it but misses.
On off, pushed to the cover region for one. 50 up for Sri Lanka as well.
On middle, nudged through mid-wicket for a quick run.
On off, blocked.
Three to end the over! Outside off, KM bunts this one through mid off and the fielder cuts it off before it touches the ropes. Three runs.
On middle, nudged to the leg side.
SLASH AND A MISS! Back of a length ball outside off, Mendis looks to cut this one away but misses it completely.
Outside off, Kusal looks to play at this but does not connect bat with ball.
Another play and a miss! On a length outside off, Mendis looks to defend this one but does not connect his blade with the ball.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sri Lanka lose two wickets and Nortje joins Ngidi in the wickets column! A soft dismissal when you look at this, a very simple catch for Ngidi. Bowls a short ball around off, Mendis looks to pull this one away but the ball takes the top edge and lobs towards the mid on region, where Ngidi runs in and takes a very good catch. Mendis falls and he will be disappointed with this.
Outside off, Chandimal does not engage. A maiden wicket for Nortje.
PLAY AND A MISS! Good start by Mulder! On a length on off, moves away after pitching, Perera swings his bat at this but only connects with thin air.
Down the leg side, left alone.
On off, played to covers.
On a length outside off, Kusal, again looks to swing his bat at this but does not connect.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mulder back into South African colours and now he gets a wicket right in his first over! Perera was looking to throw everything at the balls which had width and in that process, he loses his wicket. A back of a length ball outside off, Perera's eyes light up again as he slashes his bat at this. The ball, though takes the outside edge and goes to the left of de Kock, who has absolutely no problems in gobbling this one up. After a good start to the game, the wheels are falling off slightly for Sri Lanka.
A wicket maiden for Mulder! Angling into the right-hander, de Silva looks to push this to the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads.
On off, pushed to mid on.
Good length outside off, Dinesh has no issues in leaving this one alone.
FOUR! Chandimal gets off the mark with a boundary! On a length on off, Chandimal waits for the ball to come onto the bat and then creams his drive through the cover-point region for a boundary.
On off, Dinesh looks to block but misses.
Way outside off, DM does not want to have a piece of this.
BEATEN! On a length on off, Dinesh looks to push this one away but fails to do as the the ball goes into de Kock's gloves.
On off, de Silva is solid in his defense.
Length outside off, de Silva again looks for the block but gets beaten.
Full ball down the leg side, de Silva looks to tuck it away but misses.
FOUR! De Silva opens his accout in this game with a stylish shot! On a length on middle, de Silva lofts it over the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
On off, pushed to covers.
Outside off, punched to the cover region for a run.
On off, blocked out.
On a length on off, de Silva pushes it to point.

FOUR! A freebie from Nortje and Sipamla makes a meal of it in the deep and the visitors get a boundary! A full toss on middle, de Silva clips this one through the short fine leg region and Sipamla misfields in the deep to let this through for a boundary.
A misfield and three! On middle, pushed towards the mid-wicket region and Lungi there misfields this time and the batters collect three before he can clean up.
On off, pushed to mid on.
Outside off, Dinesh raises his blade and lets this one through to the keeper.
On off, nudged to the square leg region. De Silva wanted the single but Chandimal sent him back to the crease.
This time, they get the single! A back of a length ball on off, glanced to square leg and the run is acheived by the batters.
PLAY AND A MISS! Length ball around the fourth stump channel, Chandimal looks to push this one away but the ball zips past the blade into the keeper's mitts.
Length on off, DM again looks to block but misses.
On off, played to mid on. No run on this occasion.
On middle and leg, Dinesh looks to flick this one away but missed to get hit on the pad and the ball rolls to the leg side.
Length delivery outside off, de Silva offers no shot on this occasion.
Outside off again, left alone again.
Quick and down the leg side, de Silva looks for the flick but misses.
Short of a length ball and around off, de Silva is rushed into the shot slightly but pulls it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Length ball outside off, in the danger zone, de Silva looks to drive but fails to connect bat with ball.
FOUR! Well played by de Silva and there is scream of disappointment from Nortje! On a length on off, de Silva drives this one through the cover region for a boundary.

A loud appeal for LBW but turned down! On a length on off, nips back into the right-hander, Chandimal looked to leave that one alone but the ball goes onto hit the top of the thigh pad. An appeal but no says the umpire. There is some chatter going around but de Kock decides not to take the review on this occasion.
On off, nudged to square leg.
BEATEN! On a good length on off, the ball moves away after pitching and misses Dinesh's poke.
On middle and leg, Chandimal looks to block but misses to get hit on the pads.
Down the leg pole, DC misses his flick.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length on off, DsD looks for the defensive stroke but he misses.
On off, pushed to mid on.
Good length ball outside off, Dhananjaya looks to cut but it takes the inside edge and rolls to the off side.
Good length outside off, de Silva looks to play at this but misses.
On off, pulled to mid-wicket.
PLAY AND A MISS! Lands it outside off on a good length, moves away after pitching, de Silva looks to drive but misses it altogether.
FOUR! Too straight and Dinesh gets a boundary! On middle, Dinesh clips this one through the square leg region for a boundary. Not the start that Mulder would have wanted to this over.
Outside off, Dinesh makes no attempt to play at this.
On middle and leg, DC looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Down the leg side, DC misses his flick.
Outside off, Dinesh looks to block but misses it altogether.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a length outside off, Chandimal slashes his blade at this but misses it again.
Floated on off, pushed to the point region.
On off, tucked to mid-wicket.
Flatter and around off, de Silva guides this through the short third man region and by the time the fielder can clean up in the deep, three runs are collected.
On off, blocked.
Loopy on off, Dinesh works this through mid off for one.
On middle, defended out by de Silva. Good start by Keshav. 4 runs off his first over.
Outside off, Dinesh does not have a poke at this.
Good length ball outside off, Dinesh leaves this one alone.
Down the leg side, Chandimal looks for the tuck away but misses.
PLAY AND A MISS! Mulder bowling good lines and lengths! On a length on off, nips away, Dinesh looks to push this one away but fails to do so and the keeper collects.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, pushed to the cover region. Mulder will have to bowl this again as he had overstepped. A No Ball will follow.
On middle, clipped to the fine leg region for a single. Oh wait..another No Ball, Mulder has overstepped again. Poor from Wiaan.
On off, blocked.
On off, blocked.
Flighted on off, pushed to covers.
On off, defended well by Dinesh.
Loopy on off, Chandimal skips down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, Dinesh is solid in his defense.
Flighted around the off pole, DC works this to the cover region.
FOUR! Length delivery around the off pole, de Silva punches this one through the cover region to bag a boundary.
Yorker on off, well dug out by Dhananjaya.
Outside off, punched to the point region.
On a length on off, de Silva drives this but finds the man at mid off.

FOUR! What a cracking shot! Wonderful stroke! Overpitched on off, de Silva punches this one through the mid off region to find the ropes. Sipamla looked to block this one with his foot but he was not able to.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated on off, Dinesh drives it through wide mid off for a single.
On middle, stroked through mid on for another single.
Loopy on off, worked to long on for one.
On middle, blocked.
On off, de Silva blocks this off his front foot.
On middle, de Silva again does well to defend this one.
On a length around the off pole, Dinesh looks to block but again, he does not connect bat with ball.
On off, pushed through point for a single. 100 runs up for Sri Lanka as well. Good signs for the visitors to get to 100 in the first session of play.
On off, pulled through mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
LEG BYE! Short of a length ball on the pads, tucked to the square leg region for one. It will be a leg bye.
Outside off, de Silva lets this one through to the keeper. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Good length ball outside off, Dinesh leaves this one alone.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! First runs of the second session of play! A back of a length ball outside off, Chandimal guides this one in between gully and the third slip, where the fielder attempted to grab this one but cannot. Races away to the fence. 50-run partnership up between these two as well.
Length ball outside off, DC does not want to have a poke at this.
Outside off, Dinesh does not want to have a poke at this one.
On off, worked to the man at mid-wicket.
BEATEN! On a length on off, de Silva looks to have a taste of this but the ball goes just past the outside edge into the keeper's mitts.
On off, de Silva looks to block this one but again, does not put bat to ball.
Short of a length delivery outside off, Dhananjaya punches this one to the man at point.
Outside off, cut to point again.
Back of a length delivery outside off, de Silva looks to cut this one away but decides not to attempt the shot at the last moment and lets this one go to the keeper.
On a length on off, de Silva misses his defensive push yet again. Good start by Lungi.
On off, Dinesh fends this one back to the bowler.

FOUR! Beautifully played! Not the worst length to bowl at but Dinesh was up to the task! On a length on off and middle, Chandimal punches this one through the mid on region and it speeds away to the ropes.
Outside off, Chandimal lets this one through to the keeper.
Bumper! A short ball on middle, Dinesh ducks under this one.
Outside off, Chandimal is tempted into the drive but he is not able to connect bat with ball.
Length ball outside off, Dinesh leaves this one.
Outside off, well left by de Silva.
On off, de Silva knocks this one to point.
Nicely played and the batters collect two! On a length on off, de Silva punches this one through cover-point and will collect a couple on this occasion.

FOUR! SHOT! Dhananjaya also holds the pose for the cameras because he knew he had played this one wonderfully! A length delivery around the off pole, de Silva creams his drive through the mid on region for a boundary.
On off, pulled to mid-wicket.
Short length ball outside off, no shot offered to this delivery on this occasion.
Back of a length and on the off pole, pushed back to Anrich. A dot to start.
Full ball and outside off, Dinesh drives it well but it is well stopped by the fielder at mid off.
Outside off, left alone.

FIVE WIDES! Not the best delivery by Nortje and he concedes five wides! On a shorter length on middle, Dinesh ducks under this one and de Kock jumps, trying to grab this one but is not able to and it runs away to the ropes. Bonus runs.
Short and on the body, gets big on Chandimal, who jumps and the ball takes the top part of the blade and goes to the leg side for one.
On middle, worked to mid-wicket for one.

An appeal for LBW turned down! On a length on off, Chandimal looks to work this one away but misses to get rapped on the pads. An appeal follows but no says the umpire. There were two sounds there and it seemed to have taken the inside edge onto the pads. Quinton also does not think this is review worthy.
On off, pushed to covers.
On middle, worked to deep square leg for one.
On a length on off, DC looks to push this one away but does not connect his blade with the ball.
Three! Length on off, driven to deep covers for three runs. Good work by the fielder chasing in the deep to save a run for his side.
On off on a shorter length, de Silva pulls this one nicely to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball around off, Dinesh pushes this to mid off.

LEG BYE! On middle and leg, de Silva looks to flick it away but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls to the leg side and the batters collect a leg bye. An appeal for LBW as well by Nortje but this one was going down leg. He does not get more support from his mates. No review taken as well.
On off, tapped to covers for a quick run.
On off, played to the man stationed at point.

FOUR! Another wonderful drive by de Silva! On a length on off, Dhananjaya plays this with a straight bat through mid on for a boundary. Dinesh had to move out of the way so that the ball can go through but he did so correctly.
On off, pulled through mid-wicket for a single.

NOT OUT! A very close call but Umpire's call comes into play and Dinesh survives! A back of a length ball on off and middle, nips slightly into the right-hander, Chandimal looks to push this one away but misses to get hit on the pads. The players appeal and the umpire says no. Nortje looks the way of his skipper and de Kock makes the symbol and goes for the review. Replays roll in and it is seen that Umpire's Call is the decision on the wickets hitting. South Africa retain the review.
On middle, clipped to deep square leg for a couple.
Outside off, worked to point.
LEG BYE! On middle and leg, DC misses his flick and this goes off the pads to the leg side. A leg bye is collected.
On off, pushed to covers. No run is the call straightaway.
On off, de Silva looks to drive but it takes the inside edge and goes towards deep square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Floated on leg, worked to mid on for a quick single.
On off, blocked.
On middle, pushed through mid off for a run.
Flighted on off, defended out.
On off, pushed to short cover.
On off, driven to long off for one.
Outside off, well left by de Silva.

No Ball! Short and wide outside off, de Silva cuts this one through the point region, where the fielder gets his hands on this to slow it down. By the time, the fielder runs and collects, three runs are taken.
Down the leg side, de Silva misses his flick.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, worked to the leg side.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR DHANANJAYA DE SILVA! A very good batting show by de Silva and he deservedly gets to his fifty! His second fifty against the Proteas! He will look to continue on and turn this into a three figure number! On a length on off, de Silva punches this one through the cover region to find the ropes.
Outside off, well left by de Silva.
On off, blocked.
On off, pushed to covers.
Floated on off, pushed to covers again.
On off, solid defense by Chandimal.
Flighted around off, pushed to point for a quick run.
Short and on middle, guided to the short third man region.
On off, pushed to the off side.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a length outside off, de Silva looks to drive but the ball just about misses his outside edge.
Good length on off, pushed to the off side.
Outside off, left alone.
Another good length ball outside off, Chandimal does not think twice in leaving this one alone.
Outside off, Dinesh raises his blade and lets this one through.
On middle, tucked to square leg for one.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated on leg, tucked to the deep mid-wicket region for one.
On off, blocked.
Flighted on off, pushed to the cover region.
Flatter on middle, cut through the point region for a couple. 100-run partnership also up for these two.
Good length ball on off, defended out.
FOUR! Nicely played! Good length ball outside off, Chandimal cuts it through the point region for a boundary.
On off, Chandimal is solid in defense.
PLAY AND A MISS! Full ball outside off, Chandimal looks to drive but misses.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, de Silva defends it out.
Full on off, de Silva pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Cut and cut away nicely! Shortish and outside off, de Silva cuts it through the point region for a boundary.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, de Silva prods forward and blocks it out.
Tossed up on off, pushed to cover.
FOUR! This is poor bowling from Maharaj! Flatter ball outside off, de Silva cuts it through the cover-point region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, nudged to the square leg region.
Good length on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, DC punches this one to deep point for a single.
Length ball on off, pushed to mid-wicket.
Floated on leg, Dinesh helps it towards square leg for one.
On off, pushed to covers.
Flatter and on off, punched to mid on.

NOT OUT! South Africa review and review well but Umpire's call again means that this will remain not out! Floated on off and middle, de Silva looks to block but misses to get hit on the pads. A loud appeal follows but no says the umpire. The Proteas' players have a quick chat and decide to take this one upstairs. Replays roll in and Umpire's Call is adjudged on impact and this will remain not out. South Africa retain their review though.
SIX! Bang! Loopy ball on middle, de Silva uses his feet and lifts it over long on for a biggie.
On off, pushed to the off side for a quick single.
Outside off, left alone.
Another length ball outside off, de Silva does not engage.
On the off pole, blocked out.
Outside off, de Silva shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, punched to deep point for one.
Floated on off, de Silva pushes this one to the cover region.
On middle, blocked.
On middle, blocked out again.
On off, pushed to point.
On middle, blocked off the front foot.
FOUR! Floated on middle, de Silva camps back and punches this one through point and it races away to the ropes. Top shot.
On off, pushed to mid off.
Good length delivery outside off, slashed to deep point to rotate the strike.
Back of a length ball and on middle, clipped to the right of fine leg for a couple.
SWING AND A MISS! A back of a length ball and on off, de Silva looks to pull this one but misses it.
On off, pushed to point.
On off, tapped to covers for a quick single.
On middle, worked to mid-wicket.
On off, blocked out.
Floated and on off, Dickwella defends this one out.
Short and around off, kept out.
Outside off, blocked.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Overpitched slightly and on off, Dinesh punches this one to wide mid off and they collect one as the man there stops the ball.
Short and on off, Niroshan looks to defend this one but misses.
BEATEN! Short and around off, Dickwella looks to defend this one out but it misses the outside edge and goes into the keeper's mitts.
On off, pushed back to the mid off region.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket for one.
On off, pushed to the cover region.
Fuller and around off, Dickwella pushes this to the mid off region.
Short ball around off, Niroshan sits under this one.
Length delivery on off, Dickwella plays this to the mid off region and the batters complete a quick run.
On a length on off, Dinesh looks to block this one out but it takes the bat and just bounces next to the stumps behind. Very close. Could have easily gone onto hit the stumps.
On off, blocked.

EDGY FOUR! Not what Niroshan wanted to do but they will be glad that he found the ropes! On a length on off, Dickwella looks to block this one out but it takes the outside edge and flies in between the third slip and gully region and runs away to the ropes.
On off, well kept out.
Back of a length and on off, Dickwella looks to block this one out but misses.
Bouncer on off, ND sways away.
On off, tapped to gully.

NO BALL! Bouncer on middle, Dickwella moves away from the line of the ball and lets it through to the keeper. Sipamla will have to bowl the last ball again as he overstepped and this will be a No Ball.
Another bumper on middle, Dickwella sways away.
On off, pushed to the cover region.
Length outside off, punched to deep point for two runs.
LEG BYE! On the pads, Dinesh looks to flick but misses and the ball goes to the leg side of his pads. A leg bye is collected.
On off, pushed to point. No run is the call and they do not go for the single.
WIDE! Short one on middle, ND sways away. Wided by the umpire for the height.
Short of a length and on off, tapped to point.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball and on off, it takes the top part of the blade and goes towards the point region for a quick run.
Outside off, worked to deep point for one.
On middle, nudged to the deep square leg region for one. 200 runs up for Sri Lanka as well.
On a length on off, Dickwella pushes this to the mid off region.
FOUR! Dickwella will accept this one gleefully! On a good length on the pads, he tickles this one to the fine leg region for a boundary.
On the off pole, ND plays this to the cover region and denies the single on this occasion.
Outside off, punched to the man at short cover.
Angled into the pads, worked to deep square leg for a brace.
On off, pushed to covers.

FOUR BYES! Another short one and de Kock has no chance of getting to this! A bouncer on off and middle, Chandimal lets this one go and de Kock jumps, but is not able to catch it, runs away to the ropes.

FIFTY FOR DINESH CHANDIMAL! A very good innings to bring up his 19th Test century and a knock that was needed for Sri Lanka! On a length on off, Chandimal pushes this one to the cover region and collects a couple.
Outside off, left alone by Chandimal. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Starts off nicely with a floated delivery on off, defended.
In the air... safe! Dickwella looks to sweep but it hits the glove, lands in the short fine leg region for one.
An easy run! On off, it is pushed down to long off for one.
Nicely played! This is on middle, is played fine, the paddle scoop, towards fine leg for two.
One more single! On off, it is pushed down with the turn to long on for one.
On middle, Chandimal lunges and keeps it out.
Full and on middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Shorter and outside off, not played at.
Length again and on off, blocked. It goes off the inner half towards the leg side for one.
Length and outside off, comes back in a little. Not enough to make the batter play.
Angled into the pads, Dickwella works it through square leg for one.
Shorter and around off, it is pushed to mid off.
Dickwella comes down the track and pushes it down to long on for one.
On middle, blocked.
One more single as this is pushed down to long off.
On middle, blocked.
The sweep comes out! It is played nicely through square leg for two.
A single to end as this is pushed towards cover.
Full ball and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, nudged to the man at mid-wicket for a single.
On a length on off, Chandimal works this to mid-wicket.

EDGY FOUR! Chandimal is going along nicely now for the visitors! On a length outside off, Dinesh slashes his bat at this and the ball takes the outside edge and flies over the gully fielder into the ropes after a couple of bounces.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Down the leg side, DC misses his flick.
Floated on middle, worked to the square leg region for one.
Floated on off, pushed to the cover region. Dinesh wanted the run but Dickwella was quick to send him back.
On off, defended back onto the turf.
FOUR! Dinesh finds the gap and gets the boundary! Maharaj bowls a full toss on middle, Chandimal works this through mid-wicket and it speeds away to the ropes.
On off, pushed to mid off.

FOUR! A great way to end the over! Sri Lanka are moving along nicely now! Floated on middle, Dinesh skips down the track and works this past the man at mid on and it runs away to the ropes. 9 runs off this over.
On a length on the off pole, Dickwella drives this one nicely through covers for a brace.
Full ball outside off, Niroshan guides this one towards the gully region but the man there makes a good stop.
Another full delivery around off, worked through point for one.
Outside off on a good length, punched to the cover region.

EDGY FOUR! Again, this one evades all the fielders and runs away to the ropes! There seems to be no stopping Chandimal, by the looks of things. On a length and on off, Chandimal looks to drive this one but the ball kisses the outside edge and goes in between gully and the slip region into the ropes.
On off, pushed to covers.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a length outside off, Dickwella looks to drive but only connects his blade with thin air.
Outside off, left alone by Niroshan.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket for a single.
Good length delivery outside the off pole, pushed to the point region and the batters cross ends.
Outside off, Dinesh raises his willow and lets this one through.
Outside off again, guided to gully.
Good length ball on off, Dinesh works this to the cover region where Bavuma dives well and stops this one.
Short of a length and around off, Chandimal pushes this one to the mid off region and looks for the single but is sent back by Dickwella.
LEG BYE! On middle, DC looks to flick but misses and the ball takes the pads and goes to the leg side. The batters collect a leg bye.
FOUR! Dickwella sends one past the ropes now! On a length outside off, Dickwella slices this one through the backward point region to find the ropes. 250 up for Sri Lanka as well.
On off, pushed to covers.
Slips this down the leg side, Dickwella misses his flick though.
On off, driven to covers.
SLASH AND A MISS! On a length outside off, Chandimal looks to cut this one away but misses it altogether.
Back of a length and around off, punched to the man at mid off. Dinesh is quick to say 'No run, no run'.
On a full length around the off pole, Dinesh squeezes this one through covers for a brace.
On middle, DC works it back towards the bowler and Sipamla gets his hands on this one to slow the ball down. Just a single.
Good length delivery around off, Niroshan is solid in his defense.
On off, pushed to covers for a single.
On a length on leg, tucked away through square leg for a brace.
Slips this down the leg side, Dickwella misses his tuck away.
Down the leg side again by Mulder, Dickwella again misses his flick.
Length ball on the middle pole, worked straight to mid on. Dickwella first agreed for the single but then sent Dinesh back.
FOUR! SHOT! On a length on off, Dickwella lofts this one over the mid on region for a boundary.
Angled into middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, it is pushed to mid off.
Shorter and around off, Chandimal pushes it to covers.
Outside off and shorter in length. Chandimal looks to pull but misses.
FOUR! Short ball and put away! Can't bowl there to Chandimal. It is shorter and outside off, it is slapped through point for a boundary.
One more short ball is cut towards deep point for one. This time there is protection in the deep.
FOUR! Gift for Chandimal! It is on the pads, Chandimal says thank you very much as he works it fine on the leg side for a boundary.
A single to follow the boundary! On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Back of a length and on off, Dickwella pushes it towards cover.
FOUR! Smartly played! This is short and on middle, Dickwella waits for it and then plays it late. He plays the upper cut, it goes over the keeper for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, it is guided to point.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Bangs it short first up on middle, it is ducked under.
Shorter and around off, this is dropped towards point for one.
On middle again, this is defended onto the ground.
Another one on middle, Dickwella works it uppishly but in the gap in the mid-wicket region for one.
FOUR BYES! Way too short and on middle, Chandimal ducks under it. It goes well over the keeper for a boundary.
One more bumper, it is ducked under.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
On off again, this is pushed to mid off.
Length again and on off, Chandimal pushes it to covers.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a nasty delivery! An unplayable one, exactly what was needed to dismiss Chandimal because he was looking solid as ever. This once again, like quite a few deliveries in this gamne, rises out of nowhere. Lands on off and then takes off. Chandimal looks to fend it away by taking a hand off the handle. It flies off the glove to the widish frist slip fielder. End of a lovely knock from Chandimal but South Africa will hope this opens the floodgates.
Outside off, not played at.
Some movement now! It is on a length and around off, shapes away. Shanaka lets it be.
That has stayed low! Almost another one for South Africa! This lands outside off, Dickwella looks to defend but is stays low and sneaks below the bat.
On middle, it is defended nicely.
A short one and on middle, Dickwella evades it nicely.
One more short one and on middle, Dickwella lets it go to the keeper.
One more bumper and on middle, Dickwella lets it go over him.
Good fielding! This is fuller and around off, Dickwella pushes it towards mid off. The fielder at extra cover runs to his left and stops it.
FOUR! A lovely shot to get off the mark! This is fuller and outside off, Shanaka leans into it and creams it through covers. No chance of stopping that.
Good length and on off, Dasun keeps it out.
Fuller and around off, Shanaka looks to drive but it goes off the outer half through covers for two.
Outside off, not played at.
Length again and on middle, defended.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Shorter and outside off, Dickwella initially looks to play the upper cut but then realizes there is a fielder for that, pulls his bat back.
On middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Shorter in length and on middle, Dickwella stays back and defends it onto the ground.
On off, Dickwella gets right behind the line and pushes it to mid off.
Goes shorter in length this time, Dickwella hops and works it to mid-wicket.
A single to end the over! Short and on the body, this is pulled towards fine leg. It goes on the bounce so just the one.
The sweep comes out! It is hit to the man at short fine leg.
On middle, Dickwella works it to mid-wicket.
Another tossed up ball on middle, it is flicked to mid-wicket.
Shorter and aroud off, Dickwella strokes it to covers.
On middle, Shanaka works it to mid-wicket.
Angled into the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Full and down the leg side, helped towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! MAJESTIC! Overpitched, outside off, Dickwella leans into the shot and drives it through the covers. The fielder dives to his right, but misses the ball.

OUT! LBW! Sri Lanka lose both, a review and Dickwella, with the second new ball nearing. A pretty straight ball, which at first, seemed to be pitching outside leg. Niroshan was trying to work it to the leg side but the ball straightened a touch and kept low as well, hitting him on the pads. Mulder appealed and up went Erasmus' finger! ND immediately took the review, suggesting the ball was pitched outside leg. Ultra Edge seemed to detect a spike when ball passed the bat but closer look at the replays suggested that the bat was well away from the ball. And then came Ball Tracker. Pitched JUST about in line and hitting the stumps. Big wicket.
Outside off, Hasaranga slashes hard but misses.
On a length outside off, left alone.

EDGED, FOUR! Why isn't the slip cordon packed? Full and outside off, Hasaranga looks to drive but the ball moves away and takes the outside edge. It goes to where third slip would have been, to the third man fence.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Straight as an arrow, blocked towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around off, Shanaka looks to defend but the ball sneaks off the inside edge towards short fine leg.
Full and around off, driven back towards the bowler.
Comes down the track and drives but back to Maharaj.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Down the leg side, flick shot missed.
FOUR! MARVELLOUS! Full and outside off, Hasaranga comes on the front foot and drives it on the up through mid off! The bowler should not be too unhappy.

And that is precisely why the bowler should not be too unhappy with the previous boundary. This is pitched up, outside off, encouraging Wanindu to drive and then is shaped away to beat the outside edge.
Around off, WH feels for the ball and is beaten again.
A bit too straight, helped behind square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, pushed uppishly through point for a run.
Full and outside off, Hasaranga looks to push and run to the off side but is sent back.
Around off, solidly defended.
FOUR! What a shot. Flighted, fuller, outside off, Shanaka comes down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket. Moves to 11 from 20 balls.
Around off, watchfully blocked out.
Fuller and around off, wristed towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Around middle, helped towards short mid-wicket.
That one kicks up. Outside off, on a length, Hasaranga comes forward to defend but the ball rears up all of a sudden and pings him on the gloves. Wanindu wrings his hand in pain.
Outside off, punched through the covers for a couple. Hasaranga moves to 11 at run-a-ball.
On a length, punched through the covers for a brace again.
Full and straight, swinging in, driven straight to mid on. Is there some reverse happening?
Outside off, on a length, moving away, left alone.
Full and around off, Shanaka comes down the track and hits it straight back. Maharaj looks to pick up and throw but hurts himself. 89 balls left in the day.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Short and outside off, cut behind point for a single.
Comes from a wider angle outside off, bowls it around middle, Hasaranga defends.
FOUR! BELLIGERENT! He is not messing around. Little bit of flight, outside off, Hasaranga gets down on a knee and slog sweeps it over mid-wicket. The stand moves to 23 from 32 balls.
Around off, pushed towards long off for a run.
Full and outside off, Hasaranga looks to drive but misses.
Outside off, on a length, solidly defended.

OUT! BOWLED! Sipamla is on the board as Hasaranga chops one on. A length ball, outside off, Wanindu plays away from his body, looking to push but is defeated by the extra bounce. The ball takes the inside edge and hits the top of the bails. Sipamla is delighted. He has toiled hard all day and eventually, got a wicket.
On a length, outside off, cuts back in, Rajitha shoulders arms on length.

Whoa! That has jagged back a long way! Sipamla has got a spring in his step with that wicket. The ball is 76 overs old but still jagging around. On a length, outside off, Kasun looks to defend but the ball jags back in a long way, cuts the batsman into half, goes over the stumps and still moves a long way. De Kock does really well to dive to his left to take that. 65 minutes left in the day (extended), 79 balls to go.
Around off, on a length, well blocked out.
Full and outside off, driven towards long off for a single.
Slowly tossed up outside off, Rajitha lunges to defend but is beaten.
Risky leave. Outside off, Kasun comes forward, then goes back, thinking that the ball will turn. But the naughty ball doesn't and just goes past the off stump as Rajitha lets it go!
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Full and around off, worked through mid-wicket for a run.
Full and outside off, worked straight to short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, Shanaka looks to drive but mistimes it towards cover.
Another beauty. On a length, outside off, Rajitha looks to defend but the ball straightens and goes past the outside edge and over the stumps as well.
This one darts back in but Kasun does well to flick it towards fine leg for a single. 59 minutes left in the day (extended), 69 balls to go.
On a length, outside off, helped through mid-wicket for a run.

Bizarre, very bizarre! The South African slip cordon is smiling. On a length, wide outside off, KR misjudges the length really badly and ducks. The ball barely bounces and is taken at shin level by de Kock.
Much fuller, outside off, driven towards cover.
Tossed up, outside off, Shanaka comes down the track and pushes it towards cover.

SIX! First one of the innings! Shanaka is chancing his arm in probably the last few overs before the second new ball. Full and outside off, Dasun gets down and swings it over wide long on! Moves to 20 from 31 balls. The stand moves to 10 from 17 deliveries.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Comes down the track again, but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Outside off, chopped down to point for a single.
Full and around off, solidly kept out.
Good start. Movement through the air, fuller in length, outside off, Shanaka looks to drive but misses. 59 balls left in the day but only 22 minutes to go.
Outside off, on a length, shouldered arms to.
On a length, around off, solidly defended.
Back of a length, outside off, pushed towards cover for a single.
On a length wide outside off, easy leave for Rajitha.
That was a ripper! Frustration for Ngidi. He wants Rajitha to play, gets Rajitha to play, but then bowls wider outside off. And then, sees the ball kicking up and beat the outside edge.
And he starts with a ripper too. Nice seam position, upright, landing it on a length, just around off stump, making Shanaka play and then getting it to shape away, to beat the outside edge.
Full and wide outside off, crashed away but straight to deep point. A single taken.
Outside off, on a length, Rajitha seems to be in body-preservation mode, as he backs away to the leg side and slashes blindly. Misses.
Full and outside off, the tempter, Kasun is tempted to drive but misses the outswinger by a long margin.

UPPISH, FOUR! Almost a wicket. Outside off, on a length, Rajitha is drawn forward as he looks to push. The ball flies off the edge but is wide of gully. Races to the third man fence. 49 balls left in the day but just 15 minutes to go.
Full and outside off, KR hangs his bat well inside the line.
Oh dear... what was that? A length ball, outside off, Shanaka swings like there is no tomorrow and misses.
Fuller and just outside off, Dasun prods to defend but misses as the ball shapes away.
Another beauty. On a length, outside off, DS looks to defend but then, the ball shapes away. Is squared up and the ball beats the outside edge.
Full and jut outside off, Shanaka look to defend but is beaten by the late away shape. Get the feeling that something is going to give.
Full and around off, Dasun gets forward and pushes it towards mid on.
Full and around off, driven towards mid on.

Another one beats the edge. The inside one this time. On a length, around off, Rajitha looks to work it to the leg side but the ball shapes back in, goes in between bat and body and towards the keeper. Nortje gives a long stare to Rajitha.
Almost shows his back to the bowler but somehow, get it off the inner half of the bat towards fine leg! Takes the single and is happy to be at the other end.
Unplayabale again. Back of a length, outside off, Shanaka looks to feel for it but misses. 39 balls left in the day, but just 8 minutes to go.
Outside off, on a length, but pretty wide, let through.
Pitched up, outside off, pushed towards cover for a run.
Outside off, pushed towards mid off.
Full and outside off, driven to the left of Temba Bavuma at cover for a single.
Ouch.That has kicked off from nowhere. On a length, outside off, Rajitha looks to defend but the ball rears up from there and raps him on the glove. That would be really painful.
On a length, outside off, watchfully defended towards point.
Full and outside off, perfect line, perfect length, makes the batsman play, defeats him but cannot draw the edge!
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
Hits him again. On a length, around middle, Rajitha looks to work it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the arm. A look at the umpires and that will be it. STUMPS ON DAY 1!
LEG BYE! First runs off the day, not of the bat though! On a length on middle, Shanaka looks to work it to the leg side but he misses and the ball rolls to the leg side. A leg bye is collected.
FOUR! First boundary of the day and it is off Rajitha's bat! On a length on off, Rajitha looks to drive but it takes an outside edge and flies past gully and into the ropes for a boundary.
SWING AND A MISS! A length delivery around off, Kasun looks to work at this but misses it completely.
Back of a length on off, Kasun looks to play at this but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.

FOUR BYES! There's a bumper from Nortje and there was nothing that de Kock could do about this! A bouncer on middle, Rajitha ducks under this one and de Kock jumps but is not able to catch it and it runs away to the ropes.
Dot to end! On a length on off, KR looks to play at this but misses.
On middle, clipped towards the mid-wicket region for a couple.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! Ngidi has started off nicely! A good length delivery, just around the fourth stump channel, Dasun looks for the defensive push but gets beaten all ends up.
SIX! First biggie of the day and it is Shanaka who sends it straight to the empty stands! A short ball on middle and leg, Shanaka swivels and pulls this one to the fine leg region for a maximum.
Short of a length and on off, tapped to point.
Outside off, pushed to the cover region for a single.
On a good length and around the middle pole, Dasun clips this one through the mid-wicket region for a couple.
Good length outside off, Shanaka shoulders arms to this one.
On off, blocked to the cover region.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length on off, pushed to the cover region.
Three to end the over! On a length on off, guided through backward point for three.
On off, tucked through square leg for a single.
Length and on off, Rajitha misses his block.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length on off, played to the cover region.
Outside off, left alone.
On a good length outside off, Rajitha looks to block this one out but misses.
FOUR! On a length on off, Shanaka guides this one through the backward point region for a boundary.
On middle, clipped to the leg side for a single.
Yorker on off, pushed to the cover region. The batters think about the single but then decide not to take it in the end.

FOUR BYES! Ohhh...Nasty delivery! A bumper around off, Rajitha does well to sway away and let this one through. Quinton takes a leap of faith but it is not enough to stop the ball. The ball races away to the ropes.
On off, pushed to point for a single.
Short around off, DS sways away from this one.
Length ball and on off, Kasun is solid in his defense.
Length delivery around the fourth stump line, Kasun misses his drive, looking to play away from his body. Just where Ngidi needs to be bowling.

EDGED...SHORT! A good chance to break this partnership but this one is just short! On a length around off, Kasun looks to block but the ball takes the edge and goes towards du Plessis at first slip, but it falls just short of him.
Outside off, no shot offered to this by Rajitha.
On off, Kasun defends this one.
Full ball and around off, Rajitha works this to the man at point.
On off, pushed to point.

SIX! FIFTY FOR SHANAKA! His first one in Test cricket and this is something that he will remember! A great shot to get to this milestone as well! Slightly shorter in length and on off, Shanak swivels and hammers this one over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Outside off, left alone.

SIX! GREAT SHOT! Shanaka is looking in some touch here! There was a man there but he only sees the ball fly over him! A back of a length ball and around off, Shanaka makes room and slams it over the backward point fence for a biggie.
Outside off, cut to third man for one.
A bouncer on middle, Kasun looks to block this one but misses to get hit on the body. Must have stung slightly but nothing too serious. 13 off this over for the visitors.
On a length on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short of a length and around off, Dasun looks to block this one out but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Outside off, left alone by Shanaka.
On off, pushed to the mid on region.
An absolute jaffa! A length ball, just around the off pole, Dasun is looking to block this one but the ball just misses his outside edge and goes into de Kock's mitts.

NOT OUT! South Africa lose a review in the process and Shanaka survives! On a length on middle and leg, Shanaka looks to put bat to ball but misses to get hit on the pads. There is an appeal but no says the umpire. De Kock wants to take this one upstairs. Replays roll in and the ball is going down leg and is missing the wickets. The hosts lose a review as well.
On off, blocked.

OUT! CAUGHT! The decision to bring on Sipamla has paid dividends for the hosts and Sri Lanka lose their first wicket of Day 2! Lutho bowls this on a good length around the fourth stump channel, Rajitha is tempted into having a poke at this and does so. He can only induce an outside edge and the ball goes to the slip cordon, where Dean Elgar takes the catch.

OUT! TIMBER! What did Sipamla have for breakfast? He seems to be all up and ready for Day 2 and he has already picked 2 wickets in 2 balls now! He is also on a hat-trick now. Again, a length ball around the off pole, Fernando looks to block this one out but the ball misses his blade and goes onto rattle the off stump. He gets his third wicket of the game and it looks like the South Africans will be out to bat real soon.
Sadly, no hat-trick for him! On a length on off, Kumara blocks this one out. Also, a No Ball.
Back of a length and on off, Lahiru blocks this one out.
On off, pushed to covers.
On off, pushed to the off side. A successful over for the hosts comes to an end. Just a run and two wickets off it.
SWING AND A MISS! On a length on off, Shanaka swings his blade but misses the shot.
Another length ball outside off, moves away after pitching, Dasun throws his bat at this but again, misses his shot.
On off, DS misses his poke.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, clipped to fine leg for a single.
Down the leg side, Lahiru misses his flick.
Outside off, punched to deep point for a single.
SIX! Banged away! Sri Lanka move to 395 now! A back of a length ball and on off, Shanaka pulls this one to the deep mid-wicket region for a biggie.
On off, pushed to the mid off region. Shanaka refuses to take the single.
On middle, worked to the long on region for one.
Bouncer outside off, Lahiru sits under this one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Four-fer for Sipamla and Sri Lanka are all done for 396/9 as de Silva has been retired hurt! That seemed that it would be dropped but the man there does well to hold onto it on the fourth attempt. A back of a length ball around off, Kumara thinks about playing and then leaving and in the end, leaves his bat hanging, the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the slip region, were Rassie does well to take it on the fourth attempt after the ball seemed to be popping out of his hands.
Fernando starts with a yorker on off. Elgar blocks this one out.
On off, pushed to the leg side.
Back of a length and on off, Dean pushes it to the point region. They think about the single but do not take it in the end.
Outside off, punched to point.
On off, pushed to point.

EDGED AND SHORT! Could have been an early wicket but it was just short! On a length on off, Elgar looks to block this one out but it takes the outside edge and goes to the slip region where it falls short. A good start by Lanka. A maiden to start.
On off, played to gully.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! A good shot to open his account! On a length on off, Markram punches this one through the cover region and it runs away to the ropes. Also, a No Ball is called as Kasun had overstepped.
Pushed to the off side for a single.
FOUR! A gift to Elgar and he accepts! A full toss on middle, Elgar flicks this one through the square leg region and it races away to the ropes.
On off, blocked.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Back of a length ball and on middle, blocked out.
On off, defended out.
On a length and on off, pushed to the point region.
On middle, flicked to square leg.
FOUR! Solid shot! A full ball and around off, Aiden drives it crisply through the cover-point region and it speeds away to the ropes.
On off, blocked out.
On a length and on off, Elgar taps it towards point for a quick run.
Outside off, pushed to the cover region for one.
On off, blocked off well by Dean.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a length around off, Elgar looks to block this one out but the ball whizzes past his outside edge and into Dickwella's gloves.
FOUR! Strays on the pads this time around and Elgar just tickles this one past the keeper into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Down the leg side, Elgar misses his flick.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Back of a length around middle and leg, Aiden looks to flick this one but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. An appeal follows but no says the umpire. Looked to be going down leg.
Bouncer on off, Markram ducks under this one.
On off, pushed to covers for one.
On a length on off, pushed to the cover region to end the over.
Short of a length and around off, Aiden blocks this one towards the cover region.
Outside off, left alone. No Ball signalled.
Full ball on off, pushed to covers.
Full ball on off, Aiden defends it to cover.
Good length ball on the pads, Markram flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Fullish ball on middle and leg, Elgar works it to mid-wicket. No Ball signalled.
A length delivery outside the off pole, punched to mid off.
Another length delivery outside off, pushed to the cover fielder this time around.
FOUR! Beautiful! Just beautiful! Fullish ball on off, Markram drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Full on middle, Aiden tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Full on middle, Elgar plays it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar leaves it alone.
Fullish ball on middle, Elgar works it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Nicely bowled! Good length ball outside off, Elgar looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length ball outside off, Markram leaves it alone.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Markram is looking in good form! Full ball on middle, Markram flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Markram leaves it alone.
On off, defended out.
Outside off, left alone by Aiden.
On off, blocked out.

A good cover drive and Elgar collects three! A full length ball around off, Elgar punches this one through the cover region and the fielder does well to chase after this and stop it before it crosses the ropes. Three taken.

FOUR! Slightly lucky but Markram and South Africa won't care! On a length and around off, Aiden looks to block this one out but it kisses his outside edge and flies through the slip region and into the ropes.
Back of a length and on off, Aiden blocks it with a straight bat.
On middle, clipped to the leg side for one.
Outside off, tapped to the point region.
Short of a length and on middle, tucked to deep square leg for a couple. Good running by these two batters.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, tapped to covers.
On middle, clipped through mid-wicket for a single.
On a length on off, stroked through point for a single.
Outside off, Aiden raises his willow and lets this one through to the keeper.
Another length ball outside off, another leave by Markram.
Floated outside off, Elgar looks to block this one but misses.
On middle, worked to the off side.
Loopy on off, Dean pushes this to the cover fielder.
Tossed up on middle, clipped through mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, blocked.
Flighted ball and on off, Aiden pushes this to the man at covers. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!

NOT OUT! The Lankans were really excited about this but it goes against them and they lose a review as well! On a length on middle and off, Elgar looks to fend this one out but misses to get hit on the pads. The Sri Lankans appeal but no says the umpire. They take this one upstairs. Replays roll in and it is seen that this one was missing the stumps. The Islanders lose a review and Elgar survives.
On off, blocked.
FOUR! Well played by Dean! On a length on off, Elgar drives this one through mid off and the ball wins the race to the ropes. A wonderful shot.
Outside off, pushed to the cover region.
Yorker on off, well blocked by Elgar.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR BYES! What a bumper! A short of a length ball outside off, bounces massively after pitching and the keeper cannot stop this one as well. Races away to the ropes.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Gentle punch! A full ball on middle, Markram punches this one through the mid on region, past the man there, into the long on fence for a boundary.
Outside off, Aiden sways away.
Short of a length and on off, knocked to the leg side.
FOUR! Markram is oozing with confidence! What a stroke! A good length delivery around the off pole, Aiden hops and punches this one through the cover region to find the ropes.
Lahiru bowls a yorker this time around but AM is upto the task and digs this one out. A big over for the hosts.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
Good in length and lands it around off, Dean pushes this one to the mid off region.
Another good length delivery on middle this time, Elgar tucks this one to the deep square leg region for a single.

An appeal for lbw but no says the umpire. A length ball on middle and leg, Aiden looks to tuck it away but misses to get hit high on the thigh pad. An appeal but nothing doing says the umpire. Looked too high.
FOUR! Nicely done! Great balance shown by Markram! On a length on middle, clipped through the mid-wicket region to find the ropes. Looking very fine, is Markram.
Outside off, Aiden respects this enough to leave it alone.
On off and on a length, pushed to the cover region for one.
Outside off, no shot offered to this one by Markram.
Good length ball outside off, Aiden raises his blade and lets this one through.
In the channel outside off, left alone by AM.
Length delivery outside the off pole, Markram has patience to leave another one alone.
Changes it up and bowls a bouncer on middle, Aiden sits under this one to let it through.
On off, Elgar pushes it to the man at mid on.
On a good length on off, Elgar pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, pushed to the mid off region.
FOUR! Elgar sends one to the ropes now. Dean is good through the leg side. Strays on the pads, Elgar clips this one through square leg and it finds the ropes.
On middle, pulled to mid-wicket for one. No ball signalled.
Good length ball outside off, Aiden drops it on the off side.
Outside off, Markram misses his poke.
Yorker on off, Elgar blocks this one out.
FOUR! Worked away fine! On a length on the pads, tickled to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
On off, pushed to the mid on region.
Bouncer on off, Elgar leaves this one alone.
On off, nudged to the leg side for one.
FOUR! A good way to end the over! On the pads, clipped nicely to the fine leg region for a boundary. 9 off this over.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated on off, Elgar pushes it to the mid off region for a single.
On off, blocked.
FOUR! Another boundary for Markram! Short and wide, Markram looks to cut this one away but it takes the outside edge and flies past the first slip into the third man fence.
Flighted on off, Aiden defends this one out.
Flatter and around off, punched to the cover region.
Length delivery on off, Elgar blocks this one back to Lahiru.
On off, glanced to mid-wicket for one.
Length delivery and around off, Aiden is solid in his defense.
A full ball and on off, Aiden squeezes this one out to the point region.
A bumper over middle, Markram ducks under this one.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR AIDEN MARKRAM! His 7th in Test cricket and a well deserved one! He has played wonderfully so far and the Proteas will be pinning their hopes on him to continue on! On a length on off, Markram punches this one through point and the ball speeds away to the ropes.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Loopy on middle, nudged to the deep square leg region for a single.
Flatter and around off, Aiden rocks back and pushes it back to Wanindu.
Shortish and around off, Markram goes back and pushes it on the off side.
Full and on the stumps, defended to the on side.
Short and outside off, Markram camps back and taps it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Back of a length delivery well outside off, Dean goes after that but misses.
Fullish and angled into off and middle, flicked in front of square on the leg side for a single.

WIDE AND FOUR! There is another one of those... Short and too high. It goes well over the shoulder of Aiden Markram. The Sri Lankan keeper jumps but the ball goes over him too, and into the long stop fence. Wide as well, signalled by the umpire.

An appeal for LBW but it results in nothing. Good length ball around off, Aiden looks to play at it but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal follows but to no avail and.... Oh... Markram does well there. The ball had fallen back on the surface and sensing that it might hit the stumps, Markram pushes it away with his boot. Good sense displayed by him. Good alertness.
Length delivery around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short ball, outside off, left alone.
Lands it full outside off, it pitches and seams in, closer to off. Safe to be left alone though and Aiden does just that.
Full toss to Elgar, he drives it down straight to mid off.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to Hasaranga.

Floated on middle, glanced through mid-wicket for a single. And the 100 is up for South Africa. It is an important milestone for the openers as well. It is their 3rd 100-run stand. All of it, this season.
Shorter and around off, Markram rocks back and keeps it out.
FOUR! That is nicely played. Full and on the pads, Aiden Markram closes the face of his bat and flicks it wide of the keeper, down to the fine leg fence.
Full and around off, pushed down to long off for a single.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, driven through cover-point for a single.
Good length ball outside off, squares Dean up. He manages to defend it off the outer half to backward point.
Fullish and outside off, stabbed to cover-point.

EDGED AND FOUR! It was close to gully, by the looks of it. Good length, outside off, drawing Elgar away from his body. He does so and looks to drive but gets it off the outside edge. It goes wide of gully and down to the third man boundary.
Full and outside off, driven to mid off, who gets to his right, dives and keeps it out. Well stopped, just the single there.
Fuller and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flat and on off, Dean goes back and taps it to short mid-wicket.
On the shorter side around off, Elgar rocks back and clips it to square leg.
FOUR! Well maneuvered. Away for four. Shorter in length, around off, Elgar camps back and pulls it wide of short fine leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Excellent batting. Short and wide outside off, Dean Elgar goes on the back foot and cuts it through cover-point for a boundary.

FOUR! DEAN ELGAR GETS TO HIS 15TH TEST FIFTY! Shorter and on the off pole line, Dean Elgar rocks back and swings it through square leg. A fielder does give chase but fails to stop it. Three boundaries on the trot for Dean here.
Good length ball on off, worked to mid on for a single.
FOUR! Four more. Beautifully played. In total control there, DE. Just look at the timing there. Shortish and around off, Dean closes the face of his bat to flick it through square leg for a boundary.
Good length ball around off, Elgar closes the face of his bat and flicks it through mid-wicket. He calls for two but just gets one there.

BEATEN! Beautifull ball there. Good length delivery outside off, Aiden looks to defend but misses to do so there. The question though is, can Vishwa stay in that line? Can he bowl an over or so there?
Good length ball on the stumps, defended to the off side off the outer half.

An appeal for LBW but nothing results. Good length ball angled into middle and leg, Markram lets it be and gets hit on the pads. A mild appeal follows but to no avail. Again, height being an issue. Dimuth does not press for a review.
Full and just outside off, stabbed to mid on.
Down the leg side, Dean goes back and looks to work it behind square on the leg side, but he misses.
Floated on middle, knocked to the on side.
Flighted around off, pushed to cover.
On middle, clipped to short mid-wicket.
Floated on off, tapped to the off side.
Full and seaming in close to the off stump, Aiden leaves it alone.
Full and outside off, the right-hander shoulders arms to this one.
Full and around off, solidly defended by Markram.
Full and outside off, Aiden Markram looks to drive that on the off side but gets an inside edge onto his pads. He needs to be really careful here.
Fullish and outside off, nudged wide of point for a single.
Full and outside off, left alone by Dean there.
FOUR! That is wonderfully played. Beautiful touch. Short and wide outside off, Aiden waits and waits and then cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
FOUR! This time, through the on side. Full and on the off stump line, Markram wrists it wide of a diving mid on fielder and gets a boundary.
Shortish and around off, pushed to the off side.
Flatter and around the off stump line, defended off the outer half, to the off side.
Flat and just outside off, Aiden nudges it through the covers for one.
Floated on middle, tucked around the corner, behind square on the leg side, for a run.
Short of a length and around the middle pole, Elgar tickles this one to the deep square leg region for a single.
In the channel outside off on a good length, Markram has no issues in leaving this one alone.
Another good length delivery in the channel outside off, Aiden watchfully raises his blade and lets this one through.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sri Lanka finally get the wicket that they were searching for and they finally break this opening stand! He was looking good so far and has also scored 68 but his stint out in the middle comes to an end! Fernando dishes a good length delivery outside the off pole again. This time, Markram is tempted into the shot after being watchful in leaving balls in these areas alone. He throws his bat at this one but it proves to be his downfall. The ball takes the outside edge and flies towards Dasun Shanaka at gully, who is not going to drop this. Aiden looks at the heavens in frustration. Jersey number 68 takes out a man who was on 68.
Outside off, left alone.
Another length ball outside off, Rassie shoulders arms to this one. A good over for the Lankans comes to an end.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, helped through square leg. There is a lot of commotion, mainly from the keeper Dickwella but the single is easily completed in the end.
Outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Short and down the leg side, helped through fine leg. Good diving stop by the fielder. A single to help van der Dussen get off the mark.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Landed outside off, gentle outswing, but too wide to trouble a new batsman. Shouldered arms to.
Landed outside off, pushed through the covers for a single.
Full and outside off, coming in, watchfully pushed towards point.
Wide. A wild bouncer, way too short and high, easily ducked under.
Short and wide outside off, Elgar misses out, cutting it straight to point.
On a length outside off, coming in, pushed wide of mid off for a run.
Full and outside off, spinning in, helped through fine leg for a single. The deficit is now 249.
Shorter and quicker, outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, eased through the covers for a single.
FOUR! CLUBBED! Short and outside off, Elgar rocks back and pulls it over a ducking short leg for a boundary! 150 UP FOR SOUTH AFRICA. They trail by 244 runs. This stand is worth 11 from 19 balls now.
On middle, worked through mid-wicket for a run.
On middle and leg, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, short in length, fended to the off side.
Low full toss, outside off, driven straight to cover.
A bouncer, outside off, Rassie sways away from the line.
On a length, outside off, van der Dussen looks to drive but the ball goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Full and outside off, Elgar flicks it through mid-wicket but Dinesh Chandimal dives to his right and stops the ball.
Around off, full again, flicked straight to Chandimal this time.
Shorter in length, worked towards square leg.

FOUR! Good effort in the deep though. Full and around middle, Elgar works it through mid-wicket. The fielder comes running to his left, dives and then pushes the ball away. Now, the umpires want to check whether he has touched the ropes in doing that. The camera angles do no favour to the third umpire and it is very difficult to tell. Eventually, the third umpire seems convinced with one angle which indicates that the fielder's right shoe was touching the ropes, while his body was touching the ball. Unlucky for the fielder.
Short and down the leg side, helped through square leg for a single.
Full and around off, watchfully played out.
On a length, outside off, solidly defended.
Full and down the leg side, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
On a length, outside off, punched through the covers for a single.
A short ball, outside off, van der Dussen hops and helps it through square leg for a run. The stand moves to 20 from 36 balls.
A short ball, outside leg, now Elgar hops and tucks it through square leg for one.
A bouncer to end the over, Rassie ducks.
Full and around off, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Gentle medium pace, short of a length, wide outside off, waste of a delivery, left alone.
This is a better delivery. It is fuller, wider outside off, enticing the batsman to drive. However, van der Dussen has his wits about him and shoulders arms.

FOUR! Shanaka goes for the glory ball this time. He wants to get a full and straight, you-miss-I-hit LBW, but the angle makes the ball pitch around leg. All van der Dussen has to do is get bat on it and tickle it past the diving Dickwella to the fine leg fence. The deficit is now 229.
Outside off, on a length, let through.
Action replay of the previous delivery.
A length ball, around off, tapped to the leg side.
Fuller outside off, Elgar looks to drive but the ball barely bounces and goes beneath the bat. Does not even carry to the keeper.
FOUR! CLUNK! A short ball, outside off, Elgar gets on his toes and pulls it with aplomb through mid-wicket. Moves to 81 in 104 balls, with his 13th boundary. The stand is worth 30 now, in 47 balls.

FOUR BYES! 'Aiyyo!' is what Dickwella would be thinking about this ball. This seems more like a bouncer in frustration from Kumara and he bangs it right in the middle of the pitch. Elgar ducks but he needn't have to. The ball shoots up like a missile and poor Dickwella leaps full stretch. Gets a glove to it but can do nothing to stop the ball.
Outside off, pushed through cover for a single.
Outside off, on a length, let through.

FOUR! Meandering bowling. No pace, no length, no line. Slow, full and down the leg side, Elgar tickles it behind square leg. Poor Lahiru Kumara, who just bowled a quick over, has to run to his left and dive. Comes second best. Worse, he does not even want to get up. He looks flat. The deficit is now 216.
Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on.
Outside off, on a length, let through.
Full and outside off, Dean comes forward and presses it towards cover.
Full and outside off, DE walks across and then plays it to the leg side.
Outside off, on a length, left alone. TEA ON DAY 2, SOUTH AFRICA TRAIL BY 216!

EDGED, DOES NOT CARRY! There is that inconsistent bounce. Full and outside off, van der Dussen looks to push but there is no feet movement. Also, there is less bounce. The ball takes the outside edge but dies down on its way to the keeper.

FOUR! PRISTINE! And now, there is that inconsistent length. Kumara tries to repeat what he bowled on the previous ball but dishes out a wide half volley. This time, van der Dussen is prepared. Watches the ball carefully, leans, gets his front foot across, right to the pitch of the ball and drives it through the covers. The stand moves to 43 from 58 balls.
Outside off, a full toss, left alone.
Full and just outside off, again, this one does not bounce, Rassie adjusts by coming well forward and blocking.
Around off, on a length, defended watchfully. 229 balls left in the day.
A full-pitched ball, outside off, shouldered arms to.
On a length, outside off, pushed towards point.
Full and outside off, Elgar gets across and blocks.

FOUR LEG BYES. A bit too straight, targetting the stumps, Elgar gets across, looks to tuck but misses. However, the ball races off his back thigh, well past the keeper to the fine leg fence. The deficit is now 208.

FOUR! That is just a push. Supreme timing. Full and around middle, Elgar leans across and just clips it through mid-wicket. However, once he beats the fielder there, the ball races across the turf. 50-STAND UP IN 66 BALLS! Elgar is into the 90s now.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, pushed towards mid on this time.
Full and down the leg side, flicked towards fine leg for a single.

No idea why it took 2 minutes to bowl this ball. No discussion. No sight-screen adjustment. No field changes. Still, so much time. Sri Lanka are trying to slow the game down.  A bouncer, on middle, Elgar ducks.
A terrific short ball. Elgar is surprised and plays it very awkwardly, towards square leg.
A cracking short ball, right at the ribs but Dean plays it nicely, hopping in the air and well in front of short leg.

FOUR! Bowling to the field, reacting well with the bat but a poor effort in the field. A short ball, down the leg side, with a short leg and leg gully in place, Elgar does well to pull it all along the ground, well wide of leg gully. Now, Kusal Perera is the man at deep backward square leg. He gets to the ball but then makes a mess of it while diving. The deficit is now under 200.
That is very well fielded. A short ball, at the ribs, Elgar hops and plays it wide of short leg but the fielder dives to his left and stops the ball.

BEATEN! How many times did we use this word in the last two sessions combined? You might get those by a simple CTRL + F. Very rarely. Full and outside off, van der Dussen is forced to push at it but the ball straightens and beats the outside edge.
Around off, solidly defended.
On a length, outside off, left alone.

That is a ripper. Shaun Pollock (on air) is so impressed with this bowling, that he remarks that this entire over should be a part of the highlights package for the day! Length ball, outside off, van der Dussen commits himself into the forward push but the ball rears up suddenly. Beats him comprehensively.
Fuller and around off, well defended.
Misfield. By Lahiru Kumara. Rassie pushes this towards mid on but Kumara fumbles and the ball goes through. Two runs taken by the time he can recover.
A short ball, down the leg side, fended to leg gully.
A bumper, way too short, ducked under.
Another short ball, helped behind square leg for a single.
Outside off, on a length, let through.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.

OUT! Edged and taken by the keeper! This is what a little bit of consistency can do. Throughout the day, Sri Lanka have been struggling to be disciplined and bowl consistent lines and lengths. Since Tea, Kumara has found something and eventually, been rewarded. It is just short of full, very close to the off stump, making the batsman play at it and then, shape it away. From Rassie van der Dussen's point of view, he gets half forward. Normally, one does that when he is not sure whether to play at it or let it go. The bat just comes a little forward but in a hesitant manner. As a result, the outside edge is taken.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
Full and outside off, stays low, Elgar watches it till the last moment and pushes it towards point.
Outside off, on a length, let through.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Wow. Two wickets in the space of 5 balls. Two new batsmen in the middle. What a lift this will be to Sri Lanka's spirits. Full and outside off, Elgar looks to drive it straight back, but is unable to keep it down. Also, he is a touch away from the ball, which makes him close the bat face early. Normally, one gets away with such shots. But Shanaka is an excellent athlete. He takes a stinger to his left using both hands. Elgar cannot believe his luck. He just stands there, smiling, wishing what could have been, had he scored 5 more runs and got his 13th Test century.
And he is up and running straightaway. Around middle, on a length, de Kock whips this through mid-wicket. The fielder runs after it and stops it just inside the ropes. Three runs taken.
On middle and off, solidly defended.
FOUR! Thank you very much. Short and outside off, de Kock punches this behind point and gets his first boundary on his second ball. The deficit is now 189.
On a length, around off, watchfully defended.
Full and down the leg side, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
A bouncer, outside off, ducked under.
A full toss, outside off, worked wide of mid on. The fielder does well to get across to his right and stop the ball. A single taken to get Faf off the mark.
FOUR! De Kock has raced to 12 from 5 balls. A short ball, around middle, de Kock pulls this away nicely, through mid-wicket. The stand moves to 13 from 8 balls.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
Outside off, driven towards mid off.
Full and outside off, shoots low, watchfully kept out. 189 balls left in this session.
Down the leg side, Faf gets across and looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads.
