Around off, well blocked out.
Fuller and around off, du Plessis comes forward to defend but the ball kicks up from there. He is forced to take his bottom hand off the bat.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Outside off, pushed towards cover for a single.
A length ball, down the leg side, Faf gets across to tuck but misses. The ball misses his pads and the batsmen take a leg bye.
FOUR! CLOUT! A short ball, down the leg side, de Kock swivels and pulls it to the fine leg fence. The deficit is now 177.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Around middle, helped through mid-wicket for a run. The stand moves to 20 from 20 balls.

OUT! EDGED TO SLIP! De Kock is gone on the first ball he faces from spin. He looks totally flummoxed. Hasaranga gets his first for the match. Was this a googly? Or perhaps a leg spinner which did not spin. De Kock went on his back foot to defend but all he managed is a thick outside edge. Nice catch by substitute Lahiru Thirimanne at first slip. South Africa have lost 3/20 since Tea!
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, pushed through the covers for a single to get off the mark.
Full and outside off, du Plessis leans and drives it wide of cover for a couple.
Around off, whipped away but straight to short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, watchfully dead-batted.
On a length, outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Nice shot. Short of a length, outside off, Bavuma goes back and cuts it behind square on the off side for a boundary. The deficit is now 169.
Outside off, on a length, well defended.
On a good length, outside off, coming in a long way, Temba shoulders arms, knowing perfectly well where his off stump is.

FOUR OVERTHROWS! This helps in adding of the runs to the scoreboard. Outside off, Bavuma taps it towards point. He immediately calls for the single. Dasun Shanaka gets to it from gully, picks it up, has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. There is a back up but Lahiru Kumara at mid on gets a bad bounce and he let it through. Bavuma moves to 10 from 7 balls. The stand moves to 12 from 10 balls.
Full and around middle, stays low, Faf is hit on the pads and there is a mild LBW appeal. Turned down. Perhaps going down leg. No review thoughts. A leg bye taken.
Full and around off, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Outside off, punched wide of mid off for a single.
Flatter outside off, left alone.
On middle and off, pushed back to the bowler.
Around off, Bavuma lunges and blocks. A no ball has been signalled.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, pressed towards cover.
On a length, but wide outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, blocked towards mid-wicket.
A tad short, du Plessis looks to help it fine down the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and goes to the keeper. 159 balls left in the day, 83 minutes remaining (extended).
Outside off, left alone.
Half volley outside off, du Plessis leans and drives it through the covers but the fielder dives to his right and parries it to mid off.
On a length, outside off, let through.
A short ball, around off, pushed towards mid on.
Full and around off, eased towards mid on again.
Around off, solidly defended.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Full again, watchfully blocked out.
This stays extremely low, from a shorter length, Bavuma cuts it towards point.
Full and outside off, left alone. 149 balls left in the day, 78 minutes remaining (extended).
This one darts back in, from outside off, du Plessis defends towards mid on.
On a length, outside off, worked through mid-wicket for a single.
Another in-dipper, Bavuma looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
This is worked through square leg for a single.
Lovely delivery. On a length, outside off, du Plessis looks to cut but the ball pitches and then zooms away, to beat him.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
FOUR! That is off the edge. Landed outside off, Bavuma looks to cut but the ball spins away and takes the outside edge. It flies past slip towards third man.
Full and outside off, driven towards mid off.
Around off, pushed towards mid off.
Floated outside off, pushed towards point.
FOUR! CRACK! Interesting shot. Full and outside off, Bavuma gets down and mows a slog sweep over mid-wicket!
On a length, outside off, well defended.
On a length, outside off, worked through square leg for a couple. The deficit is now 149.
Short and outside off, punched towards cover.

FOUR! Nicely played. Full and down the leg side, du Plessis tickles it to the fine leg fence. The stand moves to 31 from 46 balls while Faf moves to double figures. 250 UP FOR SOUTH AFRICA. They now trail by 145.
On a length, outside off, solidly defended.
A short ball, outside off, let through.
FOUR! A nice gift. A low full toss, outside off, Bavuma wrists it between mid on and mid-wicket. Moves to 23 from 27 balls.
Around off, Temba lunges to defend.
Full and around off, watchfully defended. 129 balls left in the day, an hour's play left (extended).
On middle and off, well defended.
Full and outside off, solidly pressed out.
Tosed up, outside off, well kept out.
On a length, outside off, pressed towards backward point.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller, outside off, but still wide to make Faf play. He shoulders arms.
Full and just outside off, blocked towards mid on.
Another ripper. This is again, full but perhaps vey close towards off stump. FdP looks to play but the ball suddenly kicks up, beating the outside edge.

FOUR! SUBLIME! That is such a good shot in the context of what he faced on the previous ball. Kumara gets a bit too greedy and overpitches. But Faf is ready, as he drives this through mid on. The deficit is now 137.
Full and around off, watchfully defended. 119 balls left in the day, 52 minutes remaining (extended).
Outside off, pushed to the off side.
Outside off, a bit of a loop, left alone.
Landed around middle, spinning away, well defended.
Full and outside off, driven towards long off for a single. The stand moves to 40.
FOUR! Once again, Hasaranga errs on the shorter side and pays the price for it. Faf is too good a player to miss out on such lollipops. Goes back and works it through mid-wicket.
Outside off, tapped towards point for a single.
Shorter in length, pulled through mid-wicket but there is protection in the deep. Just a run. Du Plessis moves to 20 now.
Oho! Another ripper. Kumara lashes out a short ball, outside off and Bavuma has both his feet in the air, trying to evade it. That is called a rip-snorter.
Outside off, pushed towards cover.

Overpitched, around off, Temba drives it straight back but Kumara gets down against his followthrough and deflects it towards mid on, keeping the batsmen to a single. The deficit is now 129. 109 balls left in the day, 49 minutes remaining (extended).

FOUR! 50-run stand up and frustration for Kumara. He lands this on a length outside off and makes du Plessis play. He then generates an outside edge too. The ball flies past second slip and into the third man fence.
Tosed up outside off, pushed towards long off for a single.
Floated outside off, blocked to the off side.
Fuller, around middle, pushed towards long off but Hasaranga dives to his left to stop the ball.
That stays low again. It is outside off and Faf works it well, adjusting nicely, to get it through mid-wicket for a run.
Outside off, pushed towards point for one.
Full and around off, eased down to long off for another single.
On a good length, outside off, let through.
Outside off, left alone again.
Outside off, on a length, left alone. 99 balls left in the day, 41 minutes remaining (extended).
FOUR! SWEET! Too full, outside off, du Plessis leans and drives it between cover and mid off. The deficit is now 117. Faf is into the 30s now.
On a length, outside off, solidly defended.
Back of a length, outside off, shouldered arms to.
Full and around off, driven back to the bowler.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Around off, pushed towards point.
Full and outside off, pressed towards point. Bavuma wants a single but it isn't available and he is sent back.
Landed outside off, solidly dead-batted.
Outside off, pushed towards cover.
FOUR! Welcome, mate. On a length, outside off, du Plessis goes back and punches it between cover and mid off. The partnership moves to 63. 89 balls left in the day, 35 minutes to go (extended).
Outside off, closer to the stumps, left alone on a length.
Around off, helped towards mid-wicket. The batsmen take a quick single.
Another quick single. This time, Bavuma taps it in front of point.
Won't get a single there. Faf looks to dab it behind point and run but finds the fielder.
A ripper to end the over. On a length, outside off, FdP comes forward to defend but the ball shoots up suddenly and beats the outside edge.
Tossed up, around off, watchfully defended from the crease.

That is nicely played. Full and around off, Bavuma gets down and laps it towards fine leg. Kusal Perera tries his absolute best, running to his right from deep backward square leg and saves a run for his side. The deficit is now 108.
Around middle, pushed towards mid on.
Full and outside off, the googly, driven towards cover.

FOUR! Poor fielding. Short and wide outside off, du Plessis rocks back and cuts it through point. The fielder there dives to his left, Lahiru Kumara it is, but the ball goes beneath his hands. The stand moves to 72. 79 balls left in the day, 28 minutes to go.
FOUR! Another boundary! Faf is into the 40s. A touch short again, on middle, this time du Plessis works it to the other side, through mid-wicket. 11 from the over.
On a length, outside off, punched towards point.
On middle, pushed towards mid on.

Some sharp turn there. Lands it around off, it pitches and moves away sharply, beating the outside edge of Faf who looked to play at that. Short and outside off, cut in front of point for a single.
Short and outside off, dabbed to the off side.
Shortish and outside off, hit down to long off for one.
Fullish on middle, du Plessis clips it behind square on the leg side, down to fine leg. A brace. And the umpire removes the bail and says Tea. AND TEA IT WILL BE, ON DAY 3!
Full and on the pads, clipped to the on side.
Full and outside off, dabbed to the off side.

Full and outside the off pole, Keshav taps that to the off side and calls for a quick single. The fielder collects and throws it to the keeper's end. But Faf slides in and gets inside there. The ball too misses to hit the stumps though. Had it hit, might have been close.
Length delivery around off, du Plessis closes the face of his bat and glances it in front of square on the leg side for a single.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
That is an easy single there. Full and outside off, Keshav taps it to the off side for one.
Short and outside off, stroked to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up outside off, pushed down to long off for a run.
Fullish and outside off, pushed to the off side for a single.
Outside off, pushed to cover.
Full, around off, pushed down to mid on for a run. Takes Faf into the 180s.
Fullish and outside off, stabbed to point for a single.
Full and outside off, pushed down to mid off.
Fullish and outside off, stabbed to cover.
Fullish and around off, du Plessis nudges that behind square on the leg side for a couple.
Full and outside off, Faf presents the full face of his bat and drives but finds mid off there.
Fullish and outside off, du Plessis looks to power that on the off side but ends up mistiming it there.
Outside off, left alone.
Flatter and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Wanindu floats this outside off, defended to the off side. A loud 'no' from Maharaj follows there.
Floated outside off, nudged behind square on the off side for a single.
On the shorter side outside off, Faf rocks back and taps that to cover.
The 100-run partnership is up now. 3rd one in this innings for South Africa. Flat and outside off, du Plessis nudges it through the covers, to sweeper cover, for a single.
Outside off, dabbed to point.
Full and outside the off pole, blocked to the off side. Du Plessis was solid in his defence there.
Nicely played. Full and outside off, driven through the covers, to sweeper cover, for one.
Good length ball outside off, Keshav Maharaj jumps a little and taps it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, tapped down to mid off.
Full and outside off, kept out to cover. KM flashes a thumbs up to his partner at the other end, on the follow-through.
131 overs have been completed. South Africans are 577/6, with the lead now worth 181. Full and on the stumps, keeping low, defended to the on side well by Keshav.
Full and outside off, stroked straight to cover.
Full and outside the off stump, Faf du Plessis gets down and nudges it down to long off for a single. Looks like he is tired as he was looking a bit slow, when getting down.
Outside off, punched to sweeper cover for a single.
Du Plessis pushes this tossed up ball outside off through the covers for a couple.
Outside off, hit straight back to the bowler.

FOUR! Superb timing. Placement was perfect as well. Faf du Plessis now moves into the 190s with that. Shorter and outside off, FP rocks back and punches that through the covers. Places it well wide of deep extra cover as well.

Full and down the leg side, Maharaj helps it down towards fine leg. Picks up two there and gets to his 50. His 3rd in Tests. And he has a look at the heavens there. His strike rate has been very impressive too.
Short and outside off, cut through point. And they come back in for the second. Excellent running.

BEATEN! Not much of a pressure delivery though, that one. Full and outside off, Keshav Maharaj hangs his bat outside the line of the stumps, looking to defend. He though misses and the ball goes past his outside edge.
Good length ball on off, Keshav looks to work it to the leg side but gets an inside edge there. It goes off his pads, to the on side, for a single.

Ohhh.. a nasty delivery there. It is a back of a length ball outside off, it pitches and bounces sharply. Goes well past the outside edge of Faf's bat as he looked to defend that. Beats the keeper as well and goes behind him for a bye.
Good length ball on the stumps, defended.

NOT OUT! It was going to be that way when the third umpire took that long. Floats this just outside off, du Plessis prods forward to block but he misses there. The keeper, Niroshan, collects the ball and whips the bails off. They appeal for a stumping and the umpires take it upstairs to have a look. The replay is in and it is being examined multiple times. It takes a long time as it is very difficult for the third umpire to make a decision. The question - whether du Plessis' foot was in the air, when the stumping was effected - is something that looks to be very difficult to comprehend on the replays. Finally, as it is inconclusive, the third umpire deems that in the batsman's favour. Benefit of the doubt goes in the batsman's favour, remenmber?
This one is hit to deep point for a couple.
Flatter and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, nudged to point.
Flatter and around off, tapped to the off side.
Fullish and just outside off, hit down to long off for a single.
Full delivery on middle, du Plessis flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full ball on middle, du Plessis pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Good length delivery down the leg side, Maharaj lets it go.
Back of a length on middle, Maharaj pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Maharaj defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Maharaj drives it to point.
Wanindu floats this outside off, stroked firmly but straight to cover.

A vociferous appeal for LBW from Dickwella. But there was bat involved there. Flighted on off and middle, du Plessis strides forward and defends it out to the off side. Niroshan Dickwella appeals, thinking it came off the pads, but the umpire smiles it off.
Fullish and outside off, hit down to long off for a single.
Keshav defends this on off delivery to the off side.

FOUR! What a shot! And the 600 is up for the South Africans as well. Short ball, Maharaj goes back and drags this down to the long on boundary. Oh... the Proteas have batted really beautifully here. The lead now moves to 204 and it is a very difficult position, to be a Sri Lankan player.
Shortish and around off, Maharaj backs away and strokes but finds cover.
Good length ball around off, defended to point for a dot.
Short and outside off, left alone. This is good from the South Africans. They have amassed a lead, making sure that they do not come out to bat last on this Centurion wicket.
Good length ball outside off, guided down to deep backward point for a single. The lead moves to 205. Something more than enough for the Proteas to play around with.

FOUR! OMG! Keshav Maharaj! What? Hohoho..... the Rainbow Nation's dressing camp is happy alright. Short ball, Keshav stays on the back foot and pulls it ferociously over long on and gets himself a boundary.
On the pads, clipped to deep square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, stroked down to deep cover. Just the single. But Faf will keep strike. He is just 2 shy of his maiden 200 in whites now.
A flat legbreak, outside off, punched to cover.
This time, du Plessis is able to nudge it well wide of cover and takes a single. Moves to 199.
The quicker one, short and outside off, hurriedly cut to point.

The partnership between these two moves to 133 now. And that is a record. Outside off, hit down to long off for a single. This is now the highest 7th wicket partnership for the South Africans against Sri Lanka.

OUT! TAKEN! Oh my God! Du Plessis! What have you done? He has gone for the glory shot and perished here! The South African dugout cannot believe that. It has been a remarkable innings nonetheless. South Africa are now 609/7 and the lead is 213. Full and around off, Faf du Plessis looks to go big over mid on. Wanted to get to his double with a boundary. Rush of blood maybe? Whatever, the man at mid on, Karunaratne takes it and Faf cannot believe that.
Fullish and outside off, tapped to the off side.
Bouncer but down the leg side, Keshav ducks under it.
Full and down the leg side, Maharaj looks to help it down towards fine leg but fails to make any connection there.
Full and outside off, stroked firmly but straight to cover. Right then, are we going to see some aggressive strokeplay from the Saffas now?
On the pads, Keshav Maharaj looks to tickle it down to fine leg but ends up getting it off his pads. It goes down to that region and a leg bye is sneaked in.
Fullish and outside off, stabbed to backward point.

OUT! CAUGHT! So, are we in for a declaration now? Should not be long, but let's see. Anrich has lasted just 3 deliveries here. And on the 3rd, he has gotten himself out. Just a faint edge here. Fullish and outside off from around the wicket, Nortje looks to drive that through the covers but ends up getting a faint edge off the outer half. It goes behind and Niroshan Dickwella takes the easiest of catches. Fail to understand why the hosts are not declaring here! No point in continuing to push much now.
Flatter and outside off, backs away and cuts it to deep cover. A single. The fielder in the deep fumbles but luckily for Sri Lanka, does not cost them any extra runs.

OUT! LBW! Lutho Sipalma departs, on the very first ball here. It was the googly, it pitches on off and comes into Lutho. He looks to drive but to the naked eye, he seems to have missed and got hit on the pads. An appeal is put in for the LBW and the on-field umpire, after pondering for a good while, raises his finger. Sipalma, comes down, has a chat with Keshav and decides to take the review there. They have 3 reviews, so no problems in gambling with 1, with nothing much to lose. It is taken upstairs, Ultra Edge indicates that there was no bat there. In comes Ball Tracker and it seals the formality in Lanka's favour. Sipalma has to now walk back.
Very full and around off, driven down to mid on.
Full and outside off, pushed down to long off.
Full and outside off, hit down to mid off.
BEATEN! Full and outside off, Lungi prods forward and looks to block but fails to make any sort of connection there.
A well-disguised slower ball down the leg side, Maharaj looks to slog it towards deep backward square leg. Misses.
Wow, that's a good ball. It is a good challenging long hop. Keshav Maharaj goes for the pull shot but the bounce on the ball takes it over his flashing blade.
Wow, that's another excellent ball. KM going after everything here. He moved to the leg side a hint and Vishwa follows him with a full length ball. Keshav swings for the heavens but misses it.
SIX! It is a grand shot. Full-blooded swing of the bat. Full toss, Maharaj backs away and swings it mightily over deep square leg for half a dozen.
Outside off, left alone.
A single and the lead is now 222. Short ball, Keshav Maharaj goes for the pull. He gets a top edge there but it lands safely in the mid-wicket region. Takes a single and keeps strike.
Full and around off, KM mishits it down to long on. Surprisingly opts to take a single off the very first ball here.
BEATEN! That is the right length there. Full and outside off, Ngidi prods forward and looks to block but fails to do so there.
Flighted around off, pushed to the on side.

DROPPED! Maharaj telling Lungi Ngidi to calm down here. Hasaranga floats this around off, LN comes forward and strokes it uppishly and firmly towards short mid-wicket. The fielder there, dives forward but fails to hold onto that.
Full and on off, blocked.
A couple here. On off and middle, Lungi works this behind square on the leg side for two.

OUT! CAUGHT! A fine innings from Keshav comes to an end. He has hit 73 from 106 balls. A very fine knock from him. Short ball, outside off, Maharaj backs away and looks to pull that over mid-wicket. But he ends up getting a top edge there. It goes behind square on the off side, where Hasaranga gives chase and takes it later on. SOUTH AFRICA FINISH ON 621 AND LEAD BY 225 RUNS!
Good length ball on middle, flicked to deep backward square leg for a single.
Good length ball on off, blocked.
Fullish and on the pads, Kusal looks to play at it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Good length ball around off, Perera looks to play at it but misses and gets hit high on his pads.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Kusal Perera looks to play at that one but ends up getting an inside edge onto his pads.
A dot to finish then. Length ball angled into middle and leg, tucked to short leg safely.
Back of a length on middle, Karunaratne flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Down the leg side, Perera leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Perera defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length on off, Kusal keeps it out.
Length delivery outside off, Perera pushes it to point.
FOUR! Good shot! Full delivery on off, Perera drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Karunaratne blocks it off the front foot.
Short and outside off, Karunaratne looks to cut but misses it.
Length ball outside off, Karunaratne looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Good shot! Length delivery on off, Karunaratne pushes it through mid off for a boundary.
Back of a length on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.
OUT! BOWLED! Ngidi strikes! Full delivery on off, Karunaratne looks to defend but misses it and gets bowled. It hits the off stump. That ball kept low there.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Perera looks to defend but misses it.
FOUR! Terrific shot! Length ball on off, Perera punches it through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Good shot! Full delivery on middle, Perera flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Perera blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length on middle, Perera pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! Third boundary of the over! Full delivery on off, Perera drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Mendis blocks it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Mendis defends it to covers.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Mendis looks to defend but misses it.
Back of a length on middle, Mendis looks to flick but gets a leading edge. It lands safely towards point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ngidi gets his second and Sri Lanka are in trouble here! Good length delivery on off, Mendis looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards first slip where Rassie van der Dussen takes a good catch.
Full delivery on middle, Chandimal flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Good length ball outside off, dabbed to the off side. Kusal says 'ya, ya, ya' and takes a single.
Full and outside off, Dinesh lets that one be.
FOUR! Well played. Good soft hands from Chandimal. Good length ball outside off, Dinesh Chandimal angles it between third and fourth slip and the ball races away to the third man boundary.

FOUR OFF BYES! Quinton though applauds Nortje for that short ball. It was a bit too high and down the leg side, Dinesh Chandimal lets it be. De Kock jumps at full stretch but cannot stop that and the ball goes down to the fine leg fence.
Length delivery outside off, left alone there.
Fullish length ball on middle, tickled down to fine leg for a single.

Nicely played. Pushed into the off side by DC. Full and well outside off, Dinesh comes forward and gets his complete body weight behind the ball and drives it through the covers. A fielder gives chase and at the last moment, near the ropes, manages to push it back from going into the ropes. Three taken there.
Misfield and a couple. Length delivery around off, Kusal drives it to the right of mid off. The fielder gets there, dives, but fails to stop that. It goes through him and Sri Lanka pick up two.
Ohh... almost a catch there. Fullish and around off, Kusal strokes it uppishly. 'Catch' is the call to the man at mid off but it lands well ahead of him there.
FOUR! Nice shot by Perera. Shortish and outside off, Kusal Perera throws his bat at it and gets it well wide of the fielder at point for a boundary.
Angled into middle, this is worked to fine leg for a single.
An expensive over this. 14 off it. Good length ball, lands outside off and seams back in, Dinesh looks to play at it but misses and gets hit high on his pads there.

NO BALL! Wiaan oversteps on his very first ball here. The umpires wanted to have a look at that for whether it was a correct ball or a no ball. No part of Mulder's foot was behind the line, it was deemed. Full and outside off, driven to cover.
Just outside off on a length, left alone.
BEATEN! Cuts the batsman into half there. Lands it on a good length and outside off, it pitches and seams back in, Perera looks to play at it but the ball goes past his inside edge there.
Good length ball just outside off, defended to cover-point.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Nicely played. Too straight from Wiaan Mulder. It was on the pads and Kusal whips it uppishly through square leg. 'Catch' was the call but no one was there and the man at deep backward square leg runs to his right to cut off the boundary, but it was stroked well wide of him too.
Good length ball on off and middle, defended.
Outside off on a good length, dabbed to the slip cordon safely.
Fullish on middle, Chandimal is able to defend that but takes one hand off at the last minute, while doing so.
This one stays down. Shortish and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal hops and looks to drive that but ends up getting it off the inner half. It goes wide of short leg for two runs.
Full and outside off, a one-handed cover-drive is out, straight to cover.
Full and outside off, driven to point.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Just slightly overpitched. But what a beautiful example of a straight drive. It was just outside off, and DC comes forward and drives that through mid off for a boundary.

Play and a miss! That is the dangerous delivery that Perera must be aware of. It lands on a full length outside off, pitches and seams away further, goes past the outside edge of Perera as he looks to play at that.
On the pads, clipped to square leg.
Good length ball on middle, whipped to short mid-wicket. Sri Lankans pinch in a quick single here.
Good length ball on off, defended back to the bowler.
Shortish and outside off, Dinesh stands tall and punches it to the off side.
Length delivery outside off, Chandimal lets that one be. 10 overs done and the Lankans are 56/2, still trailing by 169.

BEATEN! Nicely bowled. Very nicely bowled from Ngidi. Lands it on a length and outside off, inviting Kusal Perera to drive. He does so but the ball whizzes past his outside edge and into the keeper's gloves.

NOT OUT! South Africa had 3 reviews and they have lost 1 now. Length delivery on the pads, KP looks to help it down the leg side. To the naked eye, it seems to have hit his pads and gone to Quinton de Kock behind. The South African captain and all the Saffa players appeal for a caught behind. But the umpire is unmoved. Lungi Ngidi cajoles his skipper to take a review. And Quinny, after deliberating a little does so. But Ultra Edge lays their ambitions flat as there was no spike as the ball passed the bat there.
Full and outside off, stroked firmly to cover for a single.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! The men from the Island Nation need to be positive wherever they can. Short and outside off, Dinesh chases after that one. Throws the kitchen sink at it and gets it off a thick, uppish outside edge. It flies over the slip cordon and goes down into the third man fence.
Good length ball on top of the stumps, blocked.
Full and on middle, nicely clipped through mid-wicket there, a couple. Sri Lanka need to continue to bat aggressively.
Back of a length and outside off, left alone.
Full and swinging away, to outside off, Kusal looks to work it to the leg side but ends up getting a leading edge there. It goes through the ground, down to mid on.
Great bit of fielding there from Wiaan Mulder. Full and around off, Perera drives it straight back to Wiaan, who gets down and does well to stop that.
Good length ball around off, flicked to square leg for a single. That could actually have been a chance for run out but Maharaj is right-handed and he got the ball in his left hand there.

Full and on the pads, glanced down to fine leg for one. Chandimal limps, as he gets to the other end. Gosh, Sri Lankans cannot afford another injury here. Hope he's ok and will play tomorrow. For now, IT IS STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Good carry to begin with! This is length and outside off, left alone. De Kock takes it at head height.
Length and around off, straightens a touch. Chandimal looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards gully.
FOUR! First runs for today and it is in the form of a boundary. Good shot! Length and outside off, slightly fuller. Chandimal strokes it through covers and bags a boundary.
Extra bounce again! Length and outide off, it takes off after landing and also comes in with the angle. Chandimal does well to leave it by taking his hands away.
Length and around off, defended.
A beauty to end! This lands on a length and around off, moves away after landing. Beats the outside edge of Chandimal's bat.

Where was Perera going there? This is fuller and around off, it is hit towards Bavuma at mid off. Perera wants a run and sets off. Chandimal sends him back. Luckily Bavuma fumbles and Perera gets back.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off again, left alone again.
FOUR! Through where third slip would have been! Perera's patience runs out. He goes after this one outside off, it flies off the outside edge and down to the third man fence.
Four!
Down the leg side, it is left alone. Lanka have started off positively.
Outside off and on a length. Left alone.
One more ball outside off, not played at.
Good length and on off, Chandimal defends it solidly.
Goes back to bowling outside off, not played at again.
Good length and outside off, Chandimal guides it towards point. Maharaj does really well to dive to his left and stop if.
BEATEN! Length and on off, this takes off after landing, it also moves away. Chandimal looks to defend but is beaten again.
Outside off, not played at.
Angles it away from off, left alone.

NOT OUT! That is off the back thigh! Perera survives to fight another day! Good review. On a length and around off, it comes back in after landing. Perera looks to defend but it cuts him into half. There is a noise as it goes to the keeper. An appeal and up goes the finger after a thought. He reviews and replays show it was not bat.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Length again and outside off, left alone.

A direct hit and Chandimal was a goner! Perera has to remember Chandimal is not at 100 percent and those risky singles are not the right idea. This is on a length and around off, it is played to the left of the bowler and Perera takes off. Chandimal goes for it. Mulder gets to the ball and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
A good shot but for no runs! Outside off and fuller, it is driven to wide mid off.
FOUR! Up and over! This is wide outside off and Perera goes after it. He squirts it over point and bags a boundary. Ngidi has also overstepped.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
On off, defended nicely.
Length and around off, Chandimal pushes at it but does not time it.
Length again and on off, defended solidly.
This one stays a touch low! On middle, Chandimal does well to get his bat down in time and keep it out.
Outside off, left alone.
One more ball outswide off, Perera does not play at it.
On off, it is pushed off the back foot towards cover for one.
Good length and on off, it is pushed to mid off.
On off, it is pushed to covers.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, it is kept out nicely.
One more ball on off, Perera gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
NOT OUT! Pitched outside leg easily! This is on the pad, Perera looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but turned down! South Africa review but they lose one.
On off, blocked nicely.
A yorker outside off, Perera looks to squeeze it out but gets an inside edge to the keeper.
Outside off to end, left alone.
On off, it is kept out.
Length again but outside off, left alone.
On middle, defended.
Angled into the pads, it takes off after pitching. Hits Chandimal on the pads as he tries to defend.

OUT! TIMBER There is the wicket South Africa so desperately wanted and Mulder provides it. This is on a length and outside off, it jags back in sharply. Chandimal looks to whip it in the end but fails to connect. The ball hits the off pole. The ball came back in sharply and chandimal failed to adjust to that.
On off, kept out.
Length and on off, defended.
One more length ball around off, Perera guides it through point for one.
Outside off, not played at.
Length and on off, Dickwella stays back and keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Angled into the middle pole, Dickwella looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through mid-wicket for two.
OUCH! On middle, this one takes off after landing. Perera looks to defend but it hits his elbow. He is some pain.

Leading edge and safe! A single and that brings up fifty for Perera! An entertaining knock but he needs to go on. On middle, Perera looks to flick but does so early. It goes off the leading edge through covers for one.
Outside off, Dickwella has a lazy push at it. He is beaten.
BEATEN AGAIN! Length and outside off, ND once again pushes at it away from the body. Beaten.
PUT DOWN! THat should have been taken from de Kock. This is on the pads, Dickwella looks to flick but it goes off the inner half to the right of de Kock. Who had it in his hands but fails to hang on.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for two.
Outside off, not played at.
That is a beauty! Length and around off, it pitches and moves away. Perera is beaten as he tries to defend.
Back of a length and on middle, it is defended nicely.
Down the leg side, left alone.
On off, defended.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
Lovely! Just keeps bowling it on a length around off, gets it to move away. It goes past the outside edge.
Length again, kept out again.
Lovely shot! This is fuller and outside off, Dickwella strokes it through covers. He just uses the pace and it goes through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! Through the leg side this time! It is on the pads, Dickwella works it fine on the leg side and bags a boundary.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! It is on a length and around off, angling away. Dickwella looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge and de Kock makies no mistake. So Mulder has yet another one and Sri Lanka are in deep trouble now.
Lands it on a length and on off, it is pushed to cover.
Length and around off, it is pushed to covers again.
Outside off, Perera swings but it goes off the inner half to fine leg for one.
NO BALL! Nortje oversteps! Length and around off, it is kept out.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Fuller and on off, this is hit through covers for two.
Extra bouce but outside off, left alone again.
On middle, it is worked on the leg side for one.
Good length and on off, defended.
On a length and on off, Shanaka keeps it out.
On middle, this is defended nicely.
On off, Shanaka pushes it to mid off.
length again and on off, it is kept out nicely.
On middle, it is kept out.
On the shorter side, this is pushed through covers for two.
Good length and on off, defended.
Hits the length again, defended.
On off, it is dropped towards cover for one.
The last ball is outside off, not played at.
On off, this is pushed to mid off for one. Perera batting nicely.
Outside off, left alone.
Attacks the stumps, it is defended nicely.
On off, Shanaka is solid in defense.
Another one on a length and around off, blocked.
Another one on the stumps, Dasun gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Good length around middle, it lands and comes in. Perera gets an inside edge onto the pads as he tries to defend.
A little too straight, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! On the pads, this is worked fine. The fielder at fine leg runs to his left and then dives but he touyches the rope as he pushes the ball in.

OUT! There indeed is an outside edge! That is what that noise was! Perera, who was looking so good out there, is dismissed. Nortje gets a scalp. It is on a length and around off, moves away a little. Perera hangs his bat out. There is a noise as the ball passes the bat. An appeal but turned down. It is reviewed. Replays show a spike on Ultra Edge. 111 is what they trail by.
On off, this is pushed to the off side for one.
Good length and on middle, kept out.
Back of a length and on off, it is kept out.
Good length and on off, it is pushed to mid off nicely.
Back of a length and on off, kept out nicely.
Down the leg side, it is left alone.
FOUR! Just over! This is on a length and around off, Hasaranga looks to defend, it goes off the slice and over the gully fielder for a boundary.
FOUR! This is nicely played! Short and outside off, this is cut over point and it goes away to the point boundary.
Length and around off, left alone.
On off, it is pushed to mid off.
Down the leg side, left alone.
On off, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On off, kept out.
FOUR! Through the gap! Length and around off, Hasaranga looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge past gully and to the fence.
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
Good length, kept out.
Outside off again, Hasaranga goes after it but is beaten.
Back of a length and on off, it is guided towards point for one.
Good length and on off, it is pushed to covers.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, this is driven to mid on.
A single as this is worked through mid-wicket.
On off, it is kept out nicely.
Shorter and angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for two.
On middle, defended nicely.
Loopy bakll on middle, this is defended nicely.
EDGY FOUR! Length and around off, it straightens a touch. Hasaranga looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge down to the third man fence.
Extra bounce! Hasaranga does well to defend this ball by taking a hand off the handle. It rises up off a length.

FOUR! Through the gap! Very unlucky Sipamla there! It is shorter and outside off, Hasaranga looks to cut but due to the extra bounce. It goes off the outside edgfe and between gully and third slip for a boundary.
On off, it is defended solidly.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
Length and this one stays low! Blocked.
On middle, defended.

First a catching chance and then a rin out chance too! All happening on this ball! Shanaka comes down the track and works it uppishly towards the fielder at short leg. He fails to take it. It lobs to his right. De Kock goes for it but then collects it on the bounce. He looks to underarm a throw, with his back towards the stumps at his end but misses. Would have been close.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On middle, defended nicely.
On the middle pole again, this is kept out nicely agian.
On middle, Shanaka gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
On off, this one stays a little low. Hasaranga gets his bat down in time.
On middle, this is defended nicely again.
Outside off, this is guided through point for one.
On off, this is defended nicely.
OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Another one bites the dust Length and around off, this pitches and moves away. Shanaka looks to defend but the ball kisses the outside edge and the keeper takes another catch.
On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side for two. It is actually off the pads so two leg byes.
On middle, it is kept out nicely.
On off, it is pushed through covers to the keeper.
On off, kept out.
Shorter and around off, it is guided to point.
FOUR! The slog sweep is out and it is hit brilliantly! Over the fielder at mid-wicket for a boundary.

OUT! RUN OUT! A horrible mix-up and there goes anothe wicket! This is worked towards mid-wicket. Hasaranga takes a start due to which Fernando takes off. He is though sent back from the point of no return. The fielder picks it up and throws it to the bowler who underarms it on the stumps. They take it upstairs and replays show that the batter is short.
One more ball on middle, it is kept out.
On middle, this is kept out.
On off, it is defended nicely.
On off, it is pushed to covers.
On the middle pole, it is kept out nicely.
No run, On middle, it is kept out nicely.
On middle, defended nicely.
On off, it is pushed to cover.
Quicker and on off, it is guided to point.
On middle, blocked.
On middle, it is pushed back to the bowler.
End of another quick over! On off, it is pushed to covers.
On off, it is worked to mid on.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On the middle pole, it is defended onto the ground.
Another one on middle, it is kept out nicely.
On the pads, worked to square leg.
On the pads, it is worked to square leg again.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Hasaranga makes room and then lofts this over the fielder at covers for a boundary. Lovely shot.
FOUR! Again! This time he makes room and hits it a lot flatter but gets it over cover for a boundary.
FOUR! Down the ground this time! Hasaranga steps out and smashes it down to the long on fence for a boundary.
ON middle, this is guided past third man. Hasaranga calls for two but Rajitha barely completes one.
On middle, defended.
On middle, kept out again. Good over for Lanka.
This is pushed down to long on for no runs.
On middle, blocked.
Another one on middle, Hasaranga defends it onto the ground.
Quicker and on middle, Hasaranga stays back and defends it onto the ground.

Chance of a run out but the throw is at the wrong end! On middle, this is worked to the right of the bowler. Rajitha is limping as he needs to take the single He though is sent back as that single was never going to be completed.
SIX! The field is up and it goes a long way! Hasaranga comes down the track and smashes this right off the middle and over the long on fence for a biggie.
On middle, this is blocked.
One more ball on a length Blocked.
On middle, kept out.
Outside off, comes in with the angle. Rajitha lets it be.
A low full toss on the pads, Rajitha looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Fifty for Hasaranga! A very good knock from him. He is hitting boundaries at will now! This is full and outside off, it is lofted over covers for a boundary.
Length and around off, it is defended onto the ground.
Length and on middle, this is defended onto the ground.
Outside off, Hasaranga looks to push at it. It goes off the outside edge past the gully fielder and down to the third man fence.
Good length and on middle, kept out.
FOUR! Smashed! Shorter and on middle, this is hit hard down the ground and it races away to the fence. Lovely shot.
Shorter and down the leg side, Rajitha lets it go.
Shorter and on the body, Rajitha looks to defend it by taking the eyes off the ball, does so.
Goes short again! This is defended.
Shorter in length again, Rajitha hops and keeps it out.
On the shorter side, Rajitha once again looks to keep it out without looking. He gets hit on the thigh pad.
A maiden to end! Shorter and on middle. Rajitha hops and defends it onto the ground.
Length and this one stays down low! Hasaranga looks to work it on the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

OUT! TAKEN! The hopes of avoiding an innings defeat is probably over! A length delivery, it is slapped hard but down towards long off where Hasaranga takes it. End of a good little innings from him but not enough.
Shorter and on middle, Kumara does well to duck under it. It is a no ball as the bowler has overstepped!
On middle, it is kept out.
Another one on middle, Kumara defends it onto the ground.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, it is kept out somehow.
OUT! TAKEN! End of the Test and IT IS SOUTH AFRICA WHO WIN BY AN INNINGS AND 45 RUNS! A length ball around off, Rajitha looks to fend at it but it goes off the outside edge to gully who takes it.
